text:
para reporter memilih 6 kontroversi paling buruk sepanjang tahun 2018
#
2018 adalah tahun dengan berbagai skandal di k-entertainment dengan banyak masalah kontroversial, tuntutan hukum, dan banyak lagi. sekarang dengan hanya beberapa minggu tersisa di tahun ini, wartawan dari sports today menyimpulkan orang-orang terburuk dengan kontroversi terburuk pada tahun 2018. siapa yang menurut para wartawan adalah yang terburuk tahun ini? lihatlah daftar di bawah ini: 1. yang hyun suk: pembatalan debut 'mixnine' "dengan kekuatan yg sebagai agensi, dia mengatakan dia akan membuat debut dan menempatkan peserta pelatihan dalam kompetisi, tetapi membatalkan debut mereka karena program itu gagal. dia menciptakan kontroversi dengan menanggapi geliat terakhir mereka mengambil tindakan hukum dengan gugatan balik. kemudian bahkan setahun kemudian, dia menciptakan acara audisi yang sama 'yg treasure box.' ide ironisnya mengejutkan semua orang. " - reporter yoon hye young. 2. lee seo won: pelecehan seksual "tingkah lakunya yang berani setelah pelecehan seksual, ketidaktahuan terus-menerus, dan terakhir, tindakan melarikan diri ke militer. aku terkejut 3 kali." - reporter kim sat byul 3. kim saeng min: #metoo "dia menghabiskan waktu emas yang ditunggu-tunggu dalam 25 tahun. kamu mendapatkan apa yang kamu berikan." - reporter kim na yeon 4. nancy lang x wang: pernikahan dan perceraian yang kontroversial "pembuat masalah dengan perkawinan, perkelahian, dan perceraian yang gaduh." - reporter han ye ji 5. lee jin min cp: manipulasi 'heart signal 2' "dia menciptakan program viral 'heart signal' tetapi ada juga banyak kontroversi. dia bahkan lebih mengecewakan penonton dengan perilakunya yang tidak menyenangkan dalam wawancara tentang kesalahan siaran, manipulasi dalam penyuntingan, dan banyak lagi." - reporter moon soo yeon 6. microdot: kasus lenipuan orang tua "orang tuanya berbohong kepada orang-orang di kota mereka, putranya berbohong kepada pemirsa." - reporter kim hyun min source : allkpop, oh_mestrans by : pink©ksense
link: https://koreanarea.com/2018/12/23/para-reporter-memilih-6-kontroversi-paling-buruk-sepanjang-tahun-2018/

text:
hey girl, how you doin? 😘😂🤘
i dont think you understand my excitement for this shirt. 
1. the money went to some friends awesome band(heartbreaker, it was camp dad's last show) 
2. its comfy as hell 
3. its purple(i have top colors, no favorites, and purples a top color) 
4. i am awkward often. it makes some think i do not like them, it makes some think i'm stuck up, it makes some think i'm on drugs, it makes some think...well we all know theres only a wee bit of me that gives a fuck what others think. haha 
i love supporting local artists, hopefully inget my id figured out soon. i needed this so badly. tshirts(i rarely wear them haha must be meaningful or from a memorable experience), photos, and live music are my jam. getting out to shows is really helping parts of me come out that i keep locked away. except the awkward part, that flies freely and out of control quite often. haha when i left the first thing i did on my own was go out to some local live music. it felt so fucking amazing, and feels just as amazing every time. 😊 wait what am i talking about again?? haha 😉 #awkward #awkwardaf #queer #survivor #blog #blogger #inspire #30anddivorced #living #love #happy #lgbtq #recovery #sobriety #bebold #bebrave #beyou #metoo #punk #punkrock #campdad #lifetransformation #findingme #mystory #selflove #selfcare #idgaf #notalady
name: Jessica Martin(Meier)

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

text: ✖️girls talk✖️ hannah. music photographer. “i think one of the roots of the issues with sexual assault is that women from a really young age are told to be polite and conditioned to put other people before themselves, which obviously goes hand in hand with rape culture, where coming forward about an assault may “ruin the abusers career.” men are branded with the ‘boy wonder’ stamp pretty easily, and as soon as someone brands them a genius, people stop questioning their actions, and they get away with it. by putting someone on a pedestal, they’re in the position to abuse their power and if you instil that much confidence into people for doing so little, that’s when things go wrong.” ▪️view the project at the link in bio!▪️ #photojstudent #photojournalism #girlstalkproject #portraits #nightportraits #woman #girl #sexualassault #sexualharassment #toxicmasculinity #musicscene #womeninmusic #femalephotographer #maledominatedindustry #cardiffmusicwomen #streetportrait #nightlights #metoo

text: ✖️girls talk✖️ asha. singer / songwriter. “i’ve had abuse in my general life outside the music industry but the guy was a musician and my partner at the time. he used to brag about his accomplishments in music and say ‘you’re good but you’ll never be my level’. part of it was making me feel smaller than what i was. so anything i was doing in music he would be fake supportive and that is the only man in the music industry that has ever dragged me down. he’s someone who thought he’d do way better than me and yet i’ve surpassed many of his expectations already. it was a small part of what was a really abusive situation. i got some good songs out of it though – it’s what took me on my empowering journey. i do think that i get over things a lot faster if i write about them. i just have a way of coping with my emotions and it happens to be by doing something i absolutely love.” ▪️view the project at the link in bio!▪️ #photojstudent #photojournalism #portrait #sexualassualt #sexualharassment #womeninmusic #cardiffmusicwomen #abuse #songwriting #lights #pink #girlstalkproject #ladiesofrage #streetportrait #nightlights #metoo

text: ✖️girls talk✖️ alcie. vocalist of alternative / indie band, charlie says. “sometimes you know you are getting attention for the wrong reason, but sometimes i feel like if they don’t mention your physique but they mention your voice or the overall experience, you’ve kind of gained points somehow. i often feel like i can’t dress exactly the way i want to, as i like to dress up and change character depending on the gig. i get worried people think i’m dressing for the sexual attraction.” ▪️view the project at the link in bio!▪️ #photojstudent #photojournalism #portrait #charliesays #girlstalkproject #sexualassault #sexualharassment #rape #clothing #quote #womeninmusic #cardiffmusicwomen #lighting #yellow #orange #cardiff #rain #streetportrait #nightlights #metoo

text: ✖️girls talk✖️ azzanne. girls against senior representative. "i’ve been a representative for girls against for 3 years now. when i was younger, i literally felt like these instances were just normal behaviour, so that’s why girls against is so important to me because its taught me that its not okay. we’re working on a partnership at the moment which will see security guards at venues being trained specifically in sexual harassment. i think that security guards are so focused on drugs and drinking that the issue is pushed aside. i feel sexual harassment at gigs is a reflection of a bigger problem in society, where men are brought up to think it’s okay to act a certain way but that’s also sexism within the music industry. a gig is like a microcosm of the bigger issue in the music industry which is then a microcosm of the world or society." ▪️view the project at the link in bio!▪️#photojstudent #photojournalism #portrait #nightportrait #girlstalkproject #girlsagainst #blue #lighting #sexualassault #sexualharassment #rape #musicindustry #womeninmusic #musicvenues #cardiff #organisation #gigs #streetportrait #nightlights #metoo

text: ✖️girls talk✖️ reba. dj. “i think men need to be educated on how to treat women fairly, there’s always going to be attraction but its knowing your boundaries. my body is my body it’s not for you. just cause i’m up there on a pedestal to look at and yeah i might dance and show a bit of flesh but it’s not for you to touch or grab hold of. i’m not doing it to be alluring or provocative to you. there needs to be some kind of culture shift in attitudes towards women in music and women themselves. but some men may not see it as a big thing, because it is so conditioned into our society that this is how men treat women or men adore a woman and look at them like we are their objects of desire.” ▪️view the project at the link in bio!▪️ #photojstudent #photojournalism #portrait #sexualassault #sexualharassment #dj #womeninmusic #cardiffmusicwomen #nightportrait #pink #purple #girlstalkproject #musicindustry #lighting #bumpandgrind #dj #streetportrait #nightlights #metoo

text: ✖️girls talk✖️ katie. singer of south wales based rock band, chroma. "from my personal experience outside of gigs and from being young and things have happened i didn’t necessarily want it to happen, i felt forced into situations and it's something that you carry with you for a long time. particularly when it comes to relationships then which are normal, as i’ve found i’ve been scared of a lot of things. but it’s something that you battle with a lot and it makes you a stronger person but at the end of the day, that person is unknowingly taking away an innocence or something that i should be really secure with but i’m not anymore." ▪️view the project at the link in bio!▪️ #photojstudent #photojournalism #portrait #girlstalkproject #sexualassault #sexualharassment #rape #cardiff #chroma #cardiffmusicwomen #cardiffmusicscene #womeninmusic #lighting #streetportrait #nightlights #metoo

text: ✖️girls talk✖️eadyth. bi-lingual electronic artist of r&b. "i’ve had experiences of mistreatment being a female producer, as you don’t see that many around. people say ‘oh you make music do you?’ and things like that so it can be hard you know. my opinion on the issue is that it needs to grow more, everything that’s going on at the moment needs to carry on growing and continue being recognised as men and women being equal, as well as non-binary and gender neutral people – everything needs to be neutral." ▪️view the project at the link in bio!▪️ #photojstudent #photojournalism #girlstalkproject #portrait #nightportrait #sexualassault #sexualharassment #rape #womeninmusic #cardiffmusicwomen #cardiffmusicscene #maledominatedindustry #singer #welshlanguagemusic #ladiesofrage #streetportrait #nightlights #metoo

text: ✖️girls talk✖️ yasmine. rapper from cardiff, ‘shawgz’ “i’ve had experiences when a guy has literally grabbed the mic out of my hand when i’m spitting, it’s so disrespectful. i feel like it comes down to men being jealous and intimidated when seeing a woman do ‘a man’s thing.’ all my bars now are about empowering women. i feel like my lyrics help me get through these experiences by writing about it, making tracks about it and videos about it. it’s me expressing it and forgetting about it but at the same time then also hopefully giving an insight into situations that can happen so girls don’t feel alone.” ▪️view project at link in bio!▪️ #photojstudent #photojournalism #portrait #nightportrait #girlstalkproject #sexualassault #sexualharassment #maledominatedindustry #rape #womeninmusic #cardiffmusicwomen #ladiesofrage #purple #lighting #streetportrait #nightlights #metoo

text: ✖️girls talk✖️ trishna. dj. "i work at the student union as stage crew. i mentioned i was a dj to one of the guys i work with and he looked really shocked, but he was shocked before knowing that i was doing a 'mans job'. when i’m there i don’t want people to think i’m there because i’m a groupie, or i wanna meet the band. i don’t wanna be perceived that i’m there to be sexual. and it's not like i want to prove that i can do what you can do, either. i’m here just like you, because i want a job, i want to progress in this industry. i still feel like within myself, i feel very strongly about gender conventions and things like that and i don’t want to have to live by conventions. i want the young women i know to challenge it and do what you want to do." ▪️view the project at the link in bio!▪️ #photojstudent #photojournalism #portrait #girlstalkproject #nightlife #womeninmusic #cardiffmusicwomen #femaledj #dj #sexualassault #sexualharassment #genderconventions #maledominatedindustry #sexualised #bumpandgrind #lighting #colourful #streetportrait #nightlights #metoo

text: ✖️girls talk✖️ ffion. radio dj, promoter and writer. "the touching had always been present. i remember by about 16, being somewhat resigned to these moments and understanding that if i go into the mosh pit, or if i want to be anywhere down the front to see my idols, i'd be touched or groped inappropriately. there's an onus on venues to take responsibility for what people do in their premises, if they don't take it seriously, then women have a lesser chance of the authorities taking it seriously. secondly, don't allow acts who have a history of misogyny or blatant sexism in their music or personas perform - they bring with them an audience that may reflect that behaviour." ▪️view the project at the link in bio!▪️ #photojstudent #photojournalism #portrait #nightlights #girlstalkproject #sexualassault #rape #sexualharassment #musicscene #cardiffmusicwomen #cardiffmusicscene #ladiesofrage #streetportrait #metoo

text:
@maxlaroccatribe presents
📸📸📸
🥃 sammy’s tie cocktail🥃
• • •
la moda della “tiki era” si prolunga fino alla fine degli anni 50, grazie anche alla terribile parentesi della seconda guerra mondiale, infatti le truppe impegnate nella guerra contro il giappone nel pacifico, trascorrono le brevi licenze premio…dal fronte nei bar esotici, tipici di questi luoghi e, una volta ritornati in patria, gradiscono tale ambientazione.•questo mio drink è ispirato a sammy davis junior che è stato un ballerino, cantante, batterista attore americano e che faceva parte del cosiddetto rat pack era il nome con cui negli anni cinquanta veniva chiamato il gruppo di uomini di spettacolo formato da frank sinatra, dean martin, sammy davis jr., joey bishop, e peter lawford. il rat pack si esibì spesso a las vegas, e fu una delle attrazioni che resero la città uno dei principali poli dell'intrattenimento •
🥃 sammy’s tie 🥃
50 ml gin.
15 ml grand marnier.
15 ml sciroppo di mandorla (orgeat).
17,5 ml succo di lime fresco.
•
pipetta di pimento dram.
peel di arancia.
amarena.
fiore commestibile o germoglio di menta.
servire su ghiaccio tritato.
bicchiere: rocks glass con “cravatta” di tessuto lucido.
•
il cliente potrà provare il drink così com’è oppure aggiungere il pimento dram, per un ulteriore livello di sapore rendendo il drink più speziato
•
per creare un’interazione simpatica con il cliente, si può servire al fianco di un barattolo con “aria lussuosa”  del luogo in cui si serve il drink stesso..
•••••••••••
💎ho servito per molto tempo questo drink veramente elegante nel boutique bar dell’ohla hotel di barcellona, bar che insieme al team, abbiamo portato ad essere tra i 50 migliori al mondo in soli 365 giorni
•••••••••••
🎁vorrei spiegarti come abbiamo fatto nel seminario del 10 dicembre a roma al @botanikoroma con @planetone_roma
.puoi guardare il programma sul link nella mia bio @maxlaroccatribe
•
🗣info:
.botaniko & planet one.
📩roma@planetone.it
📞+39 393 9343701 (anche whatsapp)
•
•

made by ➡️ @whats.marisa.drinking 
i recently received a bottle of japanese apricot ume liqueur from my lovely friend @kevina_c 🙏🏼 a very thoughtful birthday gift from her recent trip travels to japan. this divine liqueur is made by steeping ume fruits (while still unripe and green) in alcohol (shōchū) and sugar. it has a sweet, sour taste and was the perfect ingredient for today’s tasty tipple. happy friday and cheers to the weekend 😊
✨
✨
‘ume sour’ 
30ml roku gin @suntory_rokugin 
30ml japanese apricot liqueur 
30ml lemon juice
15ml ginger cordial 
egg white
edible flower garnish 🌸

text:
📸📸📸
from ➡️ @nickassaur ☆☆☆☆☆☆☆☆☆☆ natural historian
.
1.5 oz. terroir gin (@stgeorgespirits)
3/4 oz. lillet blanc (@lillet)
3/4 oz. green chartreuse
1/2 oz. mint syrup
3 dashes cascade celery bitters (@bittered_sling)
.
so i finally got myself a st. george spirits bottle for the home bar. of all their products, this is the one i've seen recommended the most, and after just sipping the terroir gin, i can see why it's so well-loved! it's remarkably distinct in a cocktail, but can also be enjoyed equally (or even more) on it's own.
.
the botanicals include douglas fir, california bay laurel, coastal sage, among other "evocative" botanicals. i thought cascade celery bitters would be the perfect companion for a gin which boasts aromas of evergreen forests.
.
which st. george spirits bottle should i try for next?

text:
pandan punch
.
2 oz. reposado tequila (@casamigos)
1/4 oz. vida mezcal (@delmagueymezcal)
1 oz. lime juice 
3/4 oz. pandan syrup
1/4 oz. china china (bigallet1872)
2 dashes moondog bitters (bittered_sling)
1 oz. whole milk (to clarify)
garnish with fresh pandan leaf
multiply recipe for desired number of servings
.
okay, last clarified milk punch for a while (but no promises). i was glad to finally find a piece of glassware like this available on amazon, and figured it was the perfect vessel to serve a milk punch in. if you're looking for some additional resources on how to go about making a milk punch, @barfaith has an instagram story highlight on the process, and @cocktailchemistry also just put up a video detailing milk punches. check 'em out!
.
as for the cocktail above, the reposado tequila provided a sweet, smooth base, with a touch of smoke provided by mezcal. pandan syrup for that round, almost coconut-y sweetness. lime juice for acidity and clarification. china china for complexity, and moondog bitters for a spicy element. for the choice of reposado tequila i opted for casamigos, with its honeyed notes of caramel and vanilla working well with the fragrant pandan syrup.
📸📸📸

text:
الصحفيون اختاروا أسوأ الأشخاص في عام ٢٠١٨
يانغ هيون سوك: إلغاء ترسيم “ميكس ناين”قال الصحفي يون هاي يونغ: “بالقوة التي تملكها وكالة yg، هو قال بأن الترسيم سيحدث ووضع المتدربين في منافسة فيما بينهم، لكنه ألغى ترسيمهم لأن البرنامج فشل. هو أثار جدل برده على اجراءاتهم القانونية بدعوى قضائية مضادة. ومن ثم أطلق برنامج تنافسي جديد مشابه لـ “ميكس ناين” على الرغم من أنه لم تمضي سنة كاملة حتى على انتهاء “ميكس ناين”. أفكاره الساخرة تصدم الجميع”. لي سيو وون: تحرش جنسي قال الصحفي كيم سات بيول: “تصرفه الجريء بعد قضية التحرش الجنسي، وجهله المستمر، وأخيرا، هروبه من كل شيء بالتحاقه بالجيش. لقد صُدمت لثلاث مرات”. كيم سانغ مين: حركة #metoo قال الصحفي كيم نا يون: “هو دمّر وقته الذهبي الذي طال انتظاره منذ ٢٥ عاما. أنت تحصد ما تزرعه”. نانسي لانغ x وانغ: زواج وطلاق جدلي قال الصحفي هان يي جي: “مثيران للمشاكل بزواجهما الإشكالي، وشجاراهتما، ومن ثم طلاقهما”. المقدمة لي جين مين: تلاعب بـ heart signal 2 قال الصحفي مون سو يون: “هي أنشأت البرنامج الشهير heart signal لكن كان هناك أيضا العديد من القضايا الجدلية. هي خيّبت أمل المشاهدين أكثر بسلوكها الغاضب في مقابلة أجريت معها عن أخطاء البث، والتلاعب في التحرير، والمزيد”. الرابر ميكرودوت: احتيال والديه قال الصحفي كيم هيون مين: “والديه كذبا على أهل مدينتهم، والابن كذب على المشاهدين”. @real__japan._.korea #ادمن_يمسا🍓🌸

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

text:
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text:
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text:
the #startbybelieving campaign was launched by @evawintl in april of 2011 as a way to help shift criminal justice and helping professionals’ responses to sexual assault disclosures. when @kyleclark9news and @9newsdenver brought the campaign to denver in 2014, i was proud to lend my voice and story to this important movement. as a past evawi annual conference speaker, i already knew the positive impact this basic concept was creating during potentially traumatic interactions. 
evawi’s website states: ‘start by believing’ is a philosophy that should guide our responses to sexual assault. it “flips the script” on the message victims have historically received from professionals and support people, which is: “how do i know you’re not lying?” if someone discloses to you, start by believing them. listen, support, and help locate resources if needed. you can make the difference to one person’s healing. 
we can believe in due process and support survivors. .
.
.
.
.
#tedx #tedxmilehigh #tedxmhreset #tedwomen #metoo #believesurvivors #denver

text:
tonda’s 12 days of christmas/safety tip edition:: day 9-switch up your driving route home.
•
🎄 if you feel that you are being followed, call 911. never pull over for a non-police vehicle. be aware of your exact location so you can provide it to the 911 dispatcher. •
holiday season brings more distractions and more people out and about, naturally both of these provide more opportunities for predators and criminals to take advantage of. as always, awareness is key. don’t stop taking necessary precautions when moving and shaking for 🎄😊

wie in meiner story zu sehen ist, gab’s heute einen ganz besonderen gaumenschmaus 💫
ich hab mir gedacht, es ist weihnachtszeit und wenn man ein tolles steak kauft, denkt man auch nicht lange nach, was es kostet... #vegetarisch 
für alle, die sagen, das möchte ich auch einmal zuhause genießen, hier das extrem einfache, aber sehr gute rezept:
für zwei personen:
160 g pasta 
200 ml schlagobers #sahne 
100 ml gemüse- oder hühnersuppe 
ein paar tropfen trüffelöl 
1 trüffelknolle schwarz 
60 g butter 
70 g geriebenen parmesan 
salz, weißen pfeffer, muskat 
den schlagobers mit der brühe und der butter etwas einreduzieren, währenddessen die pasta in salzwasser bissfest kochen, abseihen.
dann die sauce mit den nudeln vermengen, parmesan drunter heben, trüffel fein über die pasta hobeln, fertig 🥄
ihr lieben, wir haben es uns jetzt gemütlich gemacht, euch wünsche ich einen entspannten samstag abend und lasst es euch gut gehen 🥂😘

men don't realize how many divorces happen after home renovations. these articles will say the stress of renovations leads to divorce.

i remember having a conversation with a married woman. we had just finished fucking and her husband was blowing up her phone. she starts talking shit about him and how she can't wait to divorce after the home is done.

i asked "what do you mean after the home is done"? she told me they had started renovations in the home at her request. she jokingly told me, he wants to do anything he can to keep the marriage alive and he did this to try and make her feel a bit happier about the marriage.

side note - a marriage is directly tied to the home in many cases. coming home to a house you don't love will carry on to the marriage because the core of your marriage, memories and experiences, take place at home.

back to the game, i asked "if you still planned on divorcing him why did you let him do the he renovations" and she said because he is putting about 50k into the renovation of the kitchen and bathrooms, so it will make the value of the house go up, which means she gets more money when she divorces him and sells the home.

keep in mind this woman was in her late 40s and i was in early 20s, so i been had the red pills early. this is why i say men need to date older women and cougars cuz you will learn how women feel for real during marriage. a young bitch is still in her fantasy land stage. the cougars are way more realistic and gave marriage battles scars that have healed 10 times over.

as i always say if you have only been a lifetime boyfriend or husband you don't know women. i have learned little motives and manipulation tactics from plenty of women that have been married longer than i have been alive. 
women check out years before the husband even figured out the marriage was in trouble. renovations won't save your marriage nor will a second wedding or new car. its just more money and assets for her to gain in the divorce.

text:
#breaking story from zimbabwe—five victims at risk of being trafficked intercepted at busy bus station in harare!⠀
⠀
our staff noticed five young people grouped together at a large bus station. they caught the attention of our staff because they appeared to be nervous and hesitant. our staff decided to approach and ask the travelers some questions. but a man appeared and started answering on behalf of the travelers.⠀
⠀
he also was in possession of one, if not more, of their passports. due to these red flags, our staff intervened and involved local police in securing the interception. due to the ongoing war in their home country, the girls were unable to return to there, so our staff coordinated their temporary placement in a refugee camp in harare. ⠀
⠀
learn more about our work in zimbabwe at the link in bio. #zimbabwe #lovejustice⠀

text:
человек бежит по жизни, не жалея ног.
дом – работа, дом – работа, отбывая срок.
выходные – передышка, отпуск, как привал.
старость, пенсия, одышка, ты сюда бежал?
может выбрал изначально ты не тот маршрут?
в семь утра подъем, начальник, все ли так живут?
кто-то видит солнце, звезды, почему не ты?
руководство, производство – не до красоты.
некогда вздохнуть свободно, каждый день борьба
за краюху пенсионных. говоришь: «судьба.»
может быть, если покорно принимать ее.
душу пичкая снотворным, падать в забытье.
в мыльной пене сериалов радугу искать,
верить в старости начало и спокойно ждать.
ждать, когда окрепнут ножки у твоих детей.
по протоптанной дорожке им бежать теперь.
ты для этого родился? и за этим жил?
счастья ждал, мечтал, учился, верил и любил?
если нет, тогда, пожалуй, свой замедли бег.
и начни свой путь с начала – новый человек.
name: Nl - бизнес и здоровье

text:
you can find red pills anywhere. when i read and watch financial reports, i get more reasons not to get married than watching mgtow videos.

many men seem to think of women as angels and that's their downfall. you should view them as calculating, manipulative women that have an agenda and end game. all women have a place they want to be. that place doesn't include anyone else but themselves. the man makes 50 year plans and imagines living retired in paris with his kids in college and his wife and him running a business.

the woman imagines living retired in paris, so her whole life will be directed towards her end game.

women will think in pragmatic terms when marrying, unlike the stupid male. the man marries the romantic idealism of marriage while the woman marries the business side of it.

as it pertains to debt, in many states the debt is combined along with all the finances and assets. so it comes down to what you invested and your return on investment. marriage must be looked at as an investment more than just a business.

a woman can come into a marriage with no property, 1 kid, 400k debt and a 30k salary. let's say she marries a guy that is older has no kids, 1 home 80k debt and a 100 salary. in a divorce they will combine debt her 400k + his 80k. then split it in half if it is a community property state. so they will both have to play 240k of debt in case of divorce. the same happens with a home, if there is 200k on a house, they will have to split that.

so many women will wait until the husband pays off the house or pays all the debt and then leave him. the other way is she comes in with more debt and leaves with her debt partially paid plus him getting half of it in divorce. if a woman has 400k debt and the man has zero. he will be paying some of it off during the marriage and then will have to split the rest after divorce. so it's a win win for the woman.

on top of the debt being paid, she will get the home, child support (for the kids he didn't create) and alimony based on what he made. since most professional men downgrade when marrying (marry hot broke women, with less than them) they get screwed over.
name: PROFESSOR MGTOW

text:
final master project performance costume. 
if i am dead: he killed me :is intended to tell the story of a friend. she married a man she loved and her life descended into hell. the psychological, verbal and emotional abuse he tormented her with changed who she was fundamentally. she became what he made her into, a woman who no one would believe, listen to or help. she is left with ptsd, which is forever and keeps her from telling her story. the ptsd has scarred her permanently, and drastically effects everything. 
i share her story in memory of the girl, this woman once was, the girl who taught me how to be strong. even now as ‘damaged’ as she thinks she is, continues to teach me what true strength and the kindness of the human soul really means.

credits:
photos by emmi hyyppä
concept and realization by: dee gowans
performance by: @simonelabarga and luke biaco
choreographed by: @petalily 
produced by @agnestreplin for @lcflondon_ @unioftheartslondon 
lighting design by antony hateley
sound design by wilfred petherbridge
hair and makeup by @goshkamuah 
the most amazing technician in the world (you were right!!!): marion yarwood
thanks to: claire christie, donatella barbieri

a massive thank you to @ak liee who not only was my emotional support, but also for being my stage manager during all my chaotic rehearsals.
also thank you to @lina_aly and @oliver.to for steaming the dress for me, as well as @nashwamaatouk and oliver , for cleaning the stage of those flower petals. 
one last thank you to the amazing @julievholm , who not only had to deal with me when i was at my worst and made me laugh every chance she got, she is basically hercules. but who also helped me with many elements of testing my costume ideas and helping me sew the loops closed during the most sleep deprived hours of my life. amazing human, performer and friend.

#lcf #costume #costumedesign #metoo #domesticviolence #domesticviolenceawareness #ptsdawareness #ptsd #verbalabuse #timesup #emotionalabuse #weddingdress #wedding #applique #beading

text:
.
i am so sorry.
that my needs are my priority.
i'm sorry that i have boundaries.
and you won't always get what you want from me.
maybe many years of overgiving,
have finally made me cheap.
with my time,
my affection,
and my flexibility.
i'm sorry i can't entertain you,
and refuse to put on a show.
i'm sorry that after all this time,
i am finally saying no.
after many years of holding on,
i'm okay now with letting go.
and i'm sorry that i'm not sorry,
for prioritizing my growth.
🤷‍♀️💙🤷🏻‍♂️
.
.

text:
so we often adopt the notion that for change to be valid, it must always be grand. we burden ourselves with the expectation that we must turn our lives around overnight. we disregard the “little” things that we can do and instead choose to focus on the same go big or go home mentality that frankly keeps us stuck in our mundane ways more often than we care to admit.because breaking out of your comfort zone is not just making a drastic change and wishing for the best. it’s freeing yourself from the rigid cognitive beliefs you hold about yourself and how your life is “supposed” to be lived. it’s gaining flexibility and becoming more open to the possibility that life is ultimately a series of endless ones. sometimes, it’s as simple as realizing that there is nothing really comfortable about your “comfort zone” after all...

text:
// musician offers new way to cope with trauma //
⠀⠀
recent headlines are unearthing immense collective trauma. some folks are finally telling their stories of sexual assault after years of keeping the experiences to themselves. it only makes sense that trauma stored within our bodies can have physical effects.
⠀⠀
amber field – an sf-based vocal coach, musician, and artivist – pays careful attention to these somatic effects in their work with sound and movement.
⠀⠀
field says the term “darvo” – coined by jennifer freyd – is a helpful approach to thinking about kavanaugh and the culture of sexual assault.
⠀⠀
darvo stands for “deny, attack, and reverse victim and offender.” in essence, offenders often deflect responsibility by ping-ponging the blame back onto the victim. this is where self-blame and internalized trauma can grow. but by identifying the process and understanding how to detach and release themselves from this type of emotional manipulation, victims and people surrounding them can find ways to move forward.
⠀⠀
field believes that physical movement and sound are incredibly helpful in releasing this trauma.
⠀⠀
“darvo was an enlightening approach that gave me insight into the experience of women,” field told new sincerity. “and within our culture this was an opportunity to decide where to go next.”
⠀⠀
where do we start? we can begin to heal by shirking this trauma, manifesting a strong voice,and finally inhabiting our bodies fully.
⠀⠀
pc: stani photography
name: New Sincerity

#repost @katdperez sharing her #herlegacy2018 experience! 🧚🏾‍♀️
・・・
last year i had the honor of attending the her legacy conference & gala 2018-- a conference weekend full of panels & workshops on financial literacy, networking, and so much more, topped off with a red carpeted gala! it was one of the highlights of my year & i'm happy to say its back again on january 25th-26th at columbia university!! ✨
they've honored women such as the founder of the #metoo movement @taranajaneen, guest speakers such as the editor in chief of essence magazine, and continue to have more amazing people every year. ✨
if you'd love to be a part of this memorable weekend, head to @webelieve.inc link in bio now to get your tickets as low as $15! yes, it's only $15-- so get them before they sell out :) ✨
proceeds also benefit @webelieve.inc in allowing them to continue spreading their mission of creating the next generation of women leaders through their college chapters and middle school empowerment programs! so tag your queens 👸🏽 to join you 👇🏽✨ #webelieve #womenempowerment #networkingconference #nyc #columbiauniversity

text:
last night started out as the perfect summer night.beach,friends,snacks&even fire dancing lessons.this perfect summer night had different plans for us,though.
as my friends&i left clifton 2nd,one of us heard struggling under the trees near the steps,where the hired chairs were stacked.as we reached closer we realised we were disturbing a man who was assaulting a woman sexually.
he bolted,realising he’d been caught&to his surprise was stopped by not one woman, but two.this,although commendable,is not the point.
as some of my friends ran to catch this disgusting excuse for a human being,i fought through the chairs&bush to get to the woman who was left behind.this was while she,the real fighter,fought with what was left in her,to get to the only help that came. 
though she was a stranger,it was horrific to see her like that.what started,for her,as an innocent stroll on the beach with a boy,ended with her being dragged to a place where she was changed from a summer lover,into a victim of sexual violence.
caught up in this ‘drama’ was my friend’s 14yr old daughter.who like me,is a water baby.because of this one moment out of a million moments at one of her favourite places,she is ambivalent about going back,because of the association to this incident.not because she is unaware,like most of us,that ‘these things happen’.she is afraid because in a crowd of almost 200 people,no one helped until they saw other people doing so first. 
we were cautious,to become too involved.i guess you could say we instinctively remembered that in this sometimes ugly world-humility,bravery&kindness will always be needed.by you&by others. 
while there were respectable men with us,that contributed to diffusing this terrible situation,last night it was the women who chased the guy down.the women,(& teenage girl),that held it together&made sure we all made it out safely.that called the cops.that had no choice but to be brave enough to trust a stranger to lead them to safety.that proved to a young girl that doing what’s right will always be more important than being silent. 
it’s respect for ourselves&each other as women,as humans,that will lead us along the path to ‘salvation’.

text: 🥂never leave your drink unattended 🥂 this message is for all #woman young and old, to keep your eyes on your drinks...be safe, be aware,  be no statistic. this summer i had surgery  for my breast cancer... my lungs are so damaged i had to have operated  on awake, for my partial mastectomy with no drug  that would impede my breathing. i have stage 4 copd. the dr's  came up with their choice of drugs. i had to trust their decision , i was just outside the operating room, when they realized the block did not work...i had the only other choice. "ketamine"  or the street names  are special k, k, super c, jet, super acid green, or the "rape drug" my message to you is, you are powerless, i could not move a finger, i could not speak, yet i was aware, when talked back to reality.. i was given a tiny dose.. i was totally powerless to this drug. realizing  that this is easily found on our streets, i can say at 67 yrs. young i have endured  ketamine, i understand the affects and even trauma, not being able to move or anything, and i was safe with dr's. so this holiday season, keep your drink with you at all times🍸 and don't🍸  take a drink as a gift. be safe🍸🍷... #hamont #hamont #hamiltonont #hamiltonont #womanstrong #womansupportingwomen #sacha_hamilton #woman #christmasspirit #christmasparty #besafe #girls #drinking #drinkup #christmasspirit #copd #message #world #breastcancer #celebration #metoo #party #youngwoman #friends #positivevibes #positiveenergy #bars #houseparty #spreadtheword #drugs #besafe #womanworldwide #canada #england

8 years ago. this feels like soooo long ago. i weighed about 160-170.... but i felt beautiful... i felt strong.... i remember feeling good but the men i worked with made it unbearable. they constantly commented on my body and how ‘sexy’ i was. i work in a male dominated profession and if you said anything to anyone, you’d be a rat... but since i’ve gained weight, they started leaving me alone.... i will have a voice if it starts again though. i’m so done being anyone’s toy.
anyone else have a goal pic? share it :) #letsdothis #weightlosstransformation #weightlossjourney #loveyourself #heal #thestruggleisreal #emotionaleating #foodaddict #infertilitysucks #metoo

text:
to the women posting "selfies"... thank you for letting other young girls know that it's okay to feel beautiful with who you are 💗
.

to the moms posting a million pictures of their kids... it makes my heart so happy to see parents loving on their babies! 👶🏼👯‍♀️
.

to the married couple constantly posting "sappy love posts"... thank you for being a reminder to the next generation that all hope isn't lost and happy marriages most definitely do exist.💍
.

to the business owners who constantly post about their businesses... keep going! your strong will and passion for what you do is astounding! 💎
.

to the person posting about their fitness journey & how they decided to change their lifestyle for health reasons or just to look or feel better about themselves... i love seeing your progress pictures, your healthy meals, your gym check ins💪🏼i especially love seeing your before and after pictures!!
.

to the stay home moms posting about being able to cook and or bake for their family’s... i love seeing all you can do with your kids & all those pictures you get to take of the moments you don't want to forget. 💁🏼‍♀️
.

to the person posting quotes because they are going through something unspoken, you are in my thoughts. 💕🙏🏼
.

rejoice in the little things because in the end they were really the big things .

#happyholidays

text:
if you grew up in a family of abuse, and the abuser(s) are still there, then staying away from being with family over the holidays can be one of the most difficult decisions to make and stick to.
.
for some, holidays were the only "good times" - meaning, the only times when abuse wasn't taking place. thus, it's very easy for a survivor to glorify the holidays into this magical space where it's as if the abuse never existed, and also believe that the family you experience on that day is the only reality. but, unfortunately, the truth is that image is the furthest thing from reality.
.
this can be especially difficult to wrap your mind around if the abuse has occurred since you were a child. your brain's understanding of the world and family, was forming in the midst of these abusive relationship(s).
.
#traumabonding is a common thing to develop in those environments. even though you may be in a place today where part of you knows what your abuser(s) have done (or are doing) is wrong, you can still find yourself confused and tied to this idea that you are supposed to be with them over the holidays.
.
this makes the decision to stay away all the harder and so confusing.
.
my assault was not by a family member, but i have worked with survivors who that is their story. some are able to clearly see their abuser(s) for who they are, and others find it confusing to see them clearly.
.
abuse is about having power over someone else. it's about control. taking steps to physically distance yourself is so important to break that power, but so is emotional and mental distance.
.
survivors who have been able to break trauma bonds often say the turning point was when they decided to let the "dream" die of what their relationship with their abuser(s) could be. dreams that one day they'll stop, apologize, all will be okay.
.
**see the 2 comments below for the rest of this post**
.
 #sexualabuse #childabuse #unsafe  #familyabuse #sexualtrauma #metoo #survivor

text:
last night, the wizard of oz was on tv. it’s been one of my favorite movies since i was old enough to even have a favorite movie.
.
i tried to watch it, but i couldn’t. just hearing the cowardly lion’s initial growl made me feel sick, and that’s where i finally stopped watching.
.
but this morning, i found a few director gifts that some actors gave me when we produced wizard of oz in august. and it reminded me of all the amazing, beautiful, talented, smart, kind people i worked with on this show. and it made me fall in love with wizard of oz in a new, refreshing, and powerful way.
.
@gizmo1198 made me belly laugh at every. single. rehearsal. she gave my heart much-needed laughter and joy this summer. there is power in making people laugh, and she has a very special gift.
.
@ofsunrays made me proud to be a woman and an actor. who cares whether a man or woman plays the scarecrow? ella was the best actor for the role. she didn’t just “pull it off.” she nailed it. if she can do something hard, different, and unexpected, then so can i.
.
@aprilshowersrn helped me get through that show. without her, i may not still be here today and wizard of oz wouldn’t have happened. and yet, she was my glinda, who made me realize i had the power all along. i just had to learn it myself.
.
@thedeez gave me words of wisdom and kindness that equally helped me remember that i am brave and strong. no matter how weak and helpless i was feeling, i must have been doing something right in order for people to see me as inspiring and a good role model.
.
@s.ydneybush and i got to share the honor of performing with bravo in the final scene of his last show as an animal actor. i couldn’t have asked for a better “stage niece” to share in the reminder that i do have courage, that i will get my dogs back from that “wicked old witch,” and that “there is no place like home.”
.

i rediscovered that “home” is with my mom, dad, sister, nephews, and grandparents. i finally have that home again just in time for christmas. i’ve often wondered why they play the wizard of oz in december, but i’m so thankful they do 💖
.
.
.
.
.
#thewizardofoz #theresnoplacelikehome #safety4survivors #metoo
name: Miss Mindy 💕

text:
not only do i love what i do but it's also the why that i do it.  i love what this company is about and how we all contribute to a wonderful cause.

younique was founded in 2012 with creating funding for the younique foundation as its ultimate goal—and as the fastest-growing direct sales company in history, younique succeeded enough to make that dream a reality within two short years. 
with so many women part of the #metoo movement and unaware that this part of our company even exists, i wanted them to know there are people out there who actually care and want to help you. 
the haven retreat brings healing and hope to sexually abused women, is completely free (aside from travel), and is at an undisclosed location in utah, but they’re in the process of opening a second facility. we have products that 100% of the proceeds goes directly toward the younique foundation, and you can also round up your order to the nearest dollar. 
if you or someone you know was sexually abused before the age of 18, and they want more info, you can go to youniquefoundation.org.

the victims who attend the retreat are kept anonymous, and you do not have to be a presenter to attend. 💜

text:

they staged a flash-mob on the streets of their capital city to demand laws to eradicate street harassment, with more than a hundred girls and boys taking part! ✊✊
.
they also handed a petition to senator yasna provoste campillay calling for the criminalisation of street harassment 👏👏 .
sarah nancollas, ceo of wagggs, said this "is a great example of how girl guides are working on the international stage to change attitudes and improve the lives of girls everywhere, which is what our movement is all about. working on projects like this also gives them the skills and the confidence to be leaders." #girlguides #girlscouts #16daysofactivism #16days #advocacy #protest #flashmob #streetharassment #speakout #metoo #timesup

text:
sending someone a card, not an email, a physical card or letter  has becoming less and less popular. now the mailbox stands for business or loneliness. waiting was no longer a virtue to be praised and we are becoming less patient. i want to say that “i love you“ but i fear if those words have never travelled far through the wind and rain, can they withstand the quandary of which other people, ambition and bad timing might stand in the way. so i write letters still. each one of them is a wish/prayer i sent to myself. i say “i love you” in inky letters sealed in envelopes. i send them away and wait. counting days to see if i can learn the trick of self love before my past send me hugs in poetry. |#jin_daily #iwriteletterstomyself #sflife #mailbox #writersofinstagram

text:
my heart goes out to the poor quebec women who was murdered by the man she was dating while on vacation. leaving her 2 boys motherless because of a corrupted soul 🙏♥️😭
•
this was not what i was intending on posting today but it hits close to home for me and needed to speak about it. i was once in a manipulative abusive relationship with a narcissist who tried to isolate me from everyone i was close to and it almost destroyed me.
•
this picture was taken august 8th, 2014 one of the scariest and happiest days of my life! this was the day i secretly moved out of the aptm i shared with him right after he had gone to work. it was a fucking mission impossible operation that had been planned out for 2.5 weeks involved movers, tears, laughs and some of the bestest friends and family you could ask for!
all it took was for me to be brave enough to say, i’m not ok this is what’s happening to me at home. some of the hardest words i’ve ever had to say!
•
to all my empathic ladies out there always remember, your body, mind + soul is yours and no one elses! your mind is your own, do not let someone else manipulate it and make your decisions for you especially when it involved your famjam + friends. they’re your people and the ones who will always support you no matter what! you always have the power to reach out and ask for help even if your brain tries to convince you can’t, no one will listen and your completely alone. that’s absolute bullshit, don’t listen to it! 
that’s the inner voice the narcissist has introduces to you and even manipulated your neural pathways to destroy the solid self-esteem you once had.
•
trust me when i say this, the second you open up about the abuse your experiencing to someone you love and give in to letting go of the abuse... the snow ball effect of support you will receive is bigger then you could imagine!! i’m always here if you ever need to reach out, you are not alone, you are loved and you are enough!! 🙌💕

text:
tarc’s ride to safety program provides free transportation for anyone who needs to get to the center for women and families.

simply get onto any tarc bus in louisville or southern indiana and tell the driver you need a ride to safety. you do not need money or a tarc ticket; the ride is free. the driver will arrange for a tarc employee to meet the bus somewhere on its route who will transport you in a car to the center for women and families. you can use this free service if you’re by yourself or if you have your children with you.

for information on tarc stops and routes, visit www.ridetarc.org or pick-up a route schedule at one of the many information stands across louisville and southern indiana.

for more information about the center for women and families and the ride to safety program, call our toll-free crisis line at 1-844-237-2331.
name: Center for Women & Families

text:
“oneinthreewomen” is the proportion of european women who are victims of physical and/or sexual violence in their lifetime. ⠀
it is also the name of the first european network of companies engaged against gender-based violence, created by the kering foundation and the face foundation.⠀
⠀
on november 9th 2018, jean-paul agon, chairman and chief executive officer of l’oréal, signed the “oneinthreewomen’ commitment charter alongside with 6 other ceos of large companies. ⠀
⠀
with the signature of this european charter, companies commit to setting up specific initiatives such as raising awareness about gender-based violence and provide access to organizations that can support employees experiencing domestic violence. ⠀
⠀
l’oréal considers fighting against gender-based violence as a major society priority in which companies have to play a key role in order to tackle the issue. 💪⠀
⠀
#oneinthreewoman #ceaseproject #vaw #womenempowerment #metoo

text:
wake 👏 up 👏 america 👏

i'm stepping up on a soapbox for a minute.. i am so tired of hearing people cry about things like 'baby it's cold outside', rudolf being bullied, etc. 
um hello children are being sold into sex slavery and we are not 👏 batting 👏 an 👏 eye 👏

is it more comfortable to openly talk about stupid songs and tv shows that 'offend us', yes. is it hard to talk about absolutely horrid things that are happening right in front of us? y.e.s. but these children need a voice. 
be.
their.
voice.

young living works with hope for justice in saving trafficked victims. in august we heard about a eighteen month old girl who was rescued from sex trafficing. that should offend you. that should make you rage. that should make you want to scream and yell and flip tables. 
this is happening everywhere. 
wake. the. freak. up. america. 
#thisismypassion
#zeroapologies

hope for justice homepage > http://hopeforjustice.org/youngliving/

text:
"instagram is used as a discovery tool by almost all major agencies, meaning that “street casting” is now essentially all casting. eckhaus latta, vaquera, and demna-era balenciaga have all done street castings, but of course, rubchinskiy is best known for this kind of instagram call to action, with the designer himself reviewing the submissions."
*
"as the #metoo movement evolved over the last year and a half, it has mostly been photographers who have been #cancelled from fashion industry’s ranks. but earlier this month, street casting practices came into question after a 16-year-old boy accused russian streetwear designer gosha rubchinskiy of soliciting nude photos via instagram and the messaging platform whatsapp."
*
"while some (if not many) modeling agencies have a disconcerting past when it comes to safeguarding models’ well-being, street casting—which includes instagram casting as far as the 2010s are concerned—is muddied by its own set of ethical issues."
*
"the primary structural issue, as founder of the non-profit model alliance sara ziff sees it, is that the lack of regulation and enforcement in the modeling industry allows for purported casting calls in the first place, whether conducted in person or online—which are actually instances of outright financial scams, solicitation of child pornography, and even sex trafficking."
*
"the modeling industry does not have standards for professional conduct, even at the highest levels of the industry,” ziff says. “and lower down the food chain, for models who aren't represented, it's even more like the wild west.” and the fact that “most aspiring models are young, naive and eager to get their foot in the door, creates an environment ripe for exploitation"- alexandra mandalek, #garage #vice
*
kudos to @modelallianceny and @saraziff
who are the other innovators that are developing products to #disrupt this exploitation?
please share
#timesup 
casting all models (past, present and future) interested in changing the #businessofmodeling
*
follow @modelallianceny @saraziff
*
#formodelsbymodels 
#futureofmodels #futureofwork 
#fashiothon

you don't have to risk it all, but you have to move on, no matter what.

text:
why the pope was never affected by the #metoo movement? 
rome—pope francis on friday capped a year of sex-abuse scandals in the catholic church by vowing to “do all that is necessary” to punish abusers for their “abominations” and urging the guilty to turn themselves in. “to those who abuse minors, i would say this: convert and hand yourself over to human justice, and prepare for divine justice,” the pope told vatican officials.

the pope made the remarks in his annual christmas speech to the cardinals and bishops of the roman curia, the catholic church’s central administration, following a year of abuse scandals in the church in the u.s., latin america, europe and australia.

in his speech, the pope noted that he has called a vatican summit of bishops from around the world to discuss the abuse crisis over four days in february. the bishops will consult with experts on “how best to protect children, to avoid these tragedies, to bring healing and restoration to victims, and to improve the training imparted in seminaries.” pope francis’ credibility on fighting abuse was weakened in 2018 by widespread criticism over his prolonged support for a chilean bishop accused of covering up wrongdoing by another priest, and by accusations by a former vatican envoy to the u.s. that the pope had ignored a history of sexual misconduct by a u.s. cardinal.

the pope has declined to respond to the envoy’s accusations but has made apparent allusions to them on a number of occasions. on friday, he denounced clerics who “hide behind good intentions in order to stab their brothers and sisters in the back and to sow weeds, division and bewilderment,” comparing such people to judas, the betrayer of jesus.

pope francis said that some catholics blamed journalists for “intentionally wanting to give the false impression” that sex abuse is a problem exclusive to the church. but, he said, he was grateful to “honest and objective” members of the press who had helped uncover the problem.

text:
2018 adalah tahun skandal lainnya di k-entertainment dengan banyak masalah kontroversial tuntutan hukum, dan banyak lagi.

dengan hanya beberapa minggu tersisa di tahun ini, wartawan dari sports today memilih orang-orang terburuk dengan kontroversi terburuk pada tahun 2018. siapa yang menurut para wartawan adalah yang terburuk tahun ini? lihatlah daftar di bawah ini.

1. yang hyun suk: pembatalan debut 'mixnine'
"dengan kekuatan yg sebagai tiang, dia mengatakan akan mendebutkan dan menempatkan trainee dalam kompetisi. namun ia membatalkan debut mereka karena program itu gagal. dia menciptakan kontroversi dengan menanggapinya dengan mengambil tindakan hukum lewat gugatan balik. kemudian bahkan setahun kemudian, ia menciptakan acara audisi yang sama 'yg treasure box.' ide ironisnya mengejutkan semua orang. " - reporter yoon hye young.

2. lee seo won: pelecehan seksual
"tingkah lakunya yang berani setelah pelecehan seksual, ketidaktahuan terus-menerus, dan terakhir, tindakannya melarikan diri ke militer. aku terkejut 3 kali." - reporter kim sat byul

3. kim saeng min: #metoo
"dia menghabiskan waktu emas yang ditunggu-tunggu dalam 25 tahun. kau mendapatkan apa yang kamu berikan." - reporter kim na yeon

4. nancy lang x wang: pernikahan dan perceraian yang kontroversial
"pembuat masalah dengan perkawinan, perkelahian, dan perceraian yang gaduh." - reporter han ye ji

5 lee jin min cp: manipulasi 'heart signal 2' "dia menciptakan program viral 'heart signal' tetapi ada juga banyak kontroversi. dia bahkan lebih mengecewakan penonton dengan perilakunya yang tidak menyenangkan dalam wawancara tentang kesalahan siaran, manipulasi dalam penyuntingan, dan banyak lagi." - reporter moon soo yeon

6. microdot: penipuan orang tua
"orang tuanya berbohong kepada orang-orang di kota mereka, putranya berbohong kepada pemirsa." - reporter kim hyun min

bagaimana menurut kalian?

#koreanesia

text:
this year saw the creation of life continues after and we couldn’t be more proud of what’s been achieved so far, or more excited about what’s to come in 2019! from may to now we’ve had beautiful contributions of art, music, stories and advice from incredible contributors. 
lca’s community is ever growing and i want to thank everyone for their following and love for this project of hope and survival. lca wouldn’t be here at all without any of you guys keeping us going in fighting the good fight! 🥳 
if you want to contribute to the site in 2019 pls email or contact us on here ❤️ a special thank you to the wonderful @gentle_human for creating lca’s iconic art 🖼 •••

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates suppoed by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

cu devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

text:
in his first post-white house interviews, steve bannon, the rightwing ideologue who helped propel donald trump to the white house, made clear that he had no intention of going quietly. - i’ve got my hands back on my weapons, the former white house chief strategist, who returned as executive chairman of breitbart news late friday afternoon, told the weekly standard. - i built a f***ing machine at breitbart. and now i’m about to go back, knowing what i know, and we’re about to rev that machine up. and rev it up we will do.

just hours after his departure from the trump administration became public, breitbart, whose traffic and advertising have fallen significantly since trump’s election, trumpeted the return of their “populist hero” on its homepage. - the populist-nationalist movement got a lot stronger today, breitbart editor-in-chief alex marlow said in the publication’s announcement post. - breitbart gained an executive chairman with his finger on the pulse of the trump agenda.

the fall of steve bannon is a win for the globalists. but will it last?

also on friday, the once-again head of breitbart told bloomberg news: - if there’s any confusion out there, let me clear it up: i’m leaving the white house and going to war for trump against his opponents – on capitol hill, in the media, and in corporate america.

the 63-year-old also retains the backing of hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer. the pair met on wednesday to plot their future plans, bloomberg reported.

julia carrie wong
the guardian

text:
une amie m’a questionné sur mon obstination féministe. en retombant sur cet album, j’ai déroulé le fil d’une histoire banale. 
le féminisme d’un garçon vient d’abord de sa famille. l’environnement familial, paternel comme maternel, a influencé, nourri, fait grandir cette évidence que les inégalités femme/homme sont du sexisme et de l’oppression. 
il y a aussi ce malaise plus intime devant l’injonction masculiniste virile et bête, moins présente aujourd’hui en occident, mais encore très forte au début des années 80. le personnage du beauf du regretté cabu est un bel exemple. 
il y a ensuite la confrontation au réel: la rare inégalité que j’ai pu constater quotidiennement - et partout, dans tous les milieux, toutes les situations de vie - fut cette oppression des femmes par les hommes. quand #metoo et #balancetonporc sont arrivés, j’ai eu le sentiment que quelqu’un avait enfin allumé la lumière dans la pièce de nos vies: le sexisme domestique, professionnel, ou politique est partout. 
il y a ensuite les deux femmes les plus proches de ma vie, ma femme et ma fille. la résistance de la première, le stress paternel qui m’a envahit au plus profond de mes tripes quand la seconde est née, puis quand elle a grandi au point d’intéresser certains regards lubriques qui naturellement m’ont enragés. je ne suis plus inquiet car elle sait se défendre mieux que je ne pourrais jamais le faire. 
revenons à cet album, le plus féministe de renaud, avec cette ode aux femmes, miss maggie, et ce désarroi paternel exprimé dans mistral gagnant. le retrouver dans le placard familial m’a ouvert les yeux sur ce chemin. 
joyeux noël.

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

text:
according to a study conducted in the us, the #metoo movement encouraged by alyssa milano has contributed to a shift in public thinking about sexual harassment. the movement, in case you don't know, took off following public accusations of sexual harassment and assault against film producer harvey weinstein.
the researchers noted that the overall volume of google searches originating for this particular topic was 86 percent higher during the last eight months than what it could have been in the absence of #metoo. apparently, there were 40 to 54 million google searches related to sexual harassment or assault, which happens to be the greatest number of searches on this topic ever recorded in the u.s.

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

text:
i stumbled upon this interesting article about an ongoing debate in us over classic holiday song “baby it’s cold outside”. apparently, some people consider it has a “rapey lyric”. with radio stations and media outlets avoiding to air the song to prevent negative reactions, some even publicly banned it from their playlist. .

controversy over the song rise as a result of the #meetoo movement. a movement that aims to fight sexual violence against women that grew popular in recent year. .

while i do support the main aims of the #meetoo movement, i just think this is far fetched.
the song has been aired since 1944, originally written & performed by a married couple. dean martin, ella fitzgerald, & countless artist including michael buble did a cover on the song. have you heard the lyrics? i made a small polls asking my friends about this and 75% of them agreed that the song is fine. to me the song is cheeky, but it’s definitely not rapey. if anything it’s just a couple who passive aggressively flirting!

i do understand the importance of advocating & listening to the experiences of the abused, but in my humble opinion #metoo movement need to curate their focus better to maintain their credibility as a movement. 
________________________________________
#teatimewithadela #babyitscoldoutside #metoo

bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text:
africa has the highest prevalence rate of sexual abuse.
.
.
findings from a national survey  on violence against children in nigeria confirmed one in four females reported experiencing sexual violence in childhood with approximately 70% reporting more than one incident of sexual violence. .
.
.
in the same study, it was found that 24.8% of females’ ages 18 to 24 years experienced sexual abuse prior to age 18 of which 5.0% sought help with only 3.5% receiving any services .
.
violence against women and girls is a complete violation of human rights. .
.
the 2030 agenda promises to put an end to barriers that prevent women and girls from realising their full potential. let's join hands together to stop domestic violence, sexual abuse and rape. .
.

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates suppoed by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

cu devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
