text:
det händer hela hela tiden. senast på jobbet för någon dag sedan. en äldre främmande man tycker att jag i en hjälpsam serviceposition är någon man kan passa att på att ta på. stryka mig över armen, ner längs med ryggen, på ett sätt som markerar makt och som att han äger mig, min kropp. när jag markerar tillbaka kommer ”men lilla gumman”-blicken. ”men herregud, det är väl inte så farligt?” nej, det tyckte inte jag heller i början, när jag var yngre. men händer det 100 gånger om och du ständigt behöver vara på din vakt för att förhoppningsvis lyckas avvärja situationerna innan de händer, så rinner det tillslut över. precis som med allt annat - det krävs mindre och mindre för att man ska få nog. och har man fyllt 28 år har det tyvärr hunnit hända en hel del. för mig och för väldigt, väldigt, många andra. 
för min del har det handlat om allt ifrån att bli tagen på rumpan av de som tycker sig ha rätten till det bara för att jag råkar gå förbi, till hot, till att ha blivit våldtagen ett flertal gånger redan vid 6 års ålder. våldtäkter som varit nära att kosta mig mitt liv. allt vad rättigheter är togs ifrån mig och kvar lämnades ett trasigt tomt skal - som inte ens det var mitt längre.

har jag då fått kämpa som ett svin för att ta tillbaka, bygga upp och fylla det där skalet - min kropp - mig. ja, då får man väl välja att döma mig som säger ifrån hur mycket man vill, men det rinner över och det är väl inte konstigt? varför ska jag - vi - behöva ”stå ut” och ”inte göra en stor grej av det” när problemet ligger i att andra försöker ta makten över vad som är vårt? skulle någon sno din telefon, eller hacka sig in och ta bilder lovar jag att du skulle bli förbannad. och kan du vara förbannad över det kan du väl snälla låta oss vara förbannade och istället börja lyssna när jag tillsammans med så ofantligt många andra faktiskt ropar på hjälp att försvara det mest oersättliga vi har.

jag har en kropp, den är min och jag älskar den. låt alla få göra precis det och behandla varandra därefter. och är du en av dem som fortfarande tror att det handlar om att vi inte får röra varandra; läs igen👆

swipe❤️👉

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

text:
this was a serious business, it was actually backed by goldman sachs, but it crashed and went bankrupt because the gamers themselves who weren't cheating became enraged basically that these other people were doing, they put so much pressure on the gaming companies.

they put so much pressure on the video game companies, that they decided to basically ban gold-farming, which killed bannon's business, but it awakened him to the power of what he called "rootless white males" who spend all their time online. and five years later when bannon wound up at breitbart, he resolved to try and attract those people over to breitbart because he thought they could be radicalized in a kind of populist, nationalist way. and the way that bannon did that, the bridge between the angry abusive gamers and breitbart and pepe was milo yiannopoulous, who bannon discovered and hired to be breitbart's tech editor.

from the time i met him in 2011, he's had exactly the same politics. the same stuff you heard from trump, you saw on the campaign trail. what he was looking for was a vessel because nobody in republican washington believed in these kinds of ideas. the whole trend in the republican party was toward liberalizing immigration laws, passing comprehensive immigration reform. he was against it.

joshua green
devil's bargain: steve bannon, donald trump, and the storming of the presidency

text:
a few months later, in autumn 2013, wylie met steve bannon. at the time, he was editor-in-chief of breitbart, which he had brought to britain to support his friend nigel farage in his mission to take britain out of the european union.

what was he like? - smart, says wylie. - interesting. really interested in ideas. he’s the only straight man i’ve ever talked to about intersectional feminist theory. he saw its relevance straightaway to the oppressions that conservative, young white men feel.

wylie meeting bannon was the moment petrol was poured on a flickering flame. wylie lives for ideas. he speaks 19 to the dozen for hours at a time. he had a theory to prove. and at the time, this was a purely intellectual problem. politics was like fashion, he told bannon.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

text:
@ghosthunterthemovie love seeing this in stores! have you seen #ghosthuntermovie yet? a glimpse into my life..a massive branch from a tree who has grown many experiencing many highs and lows throughout my life. people wonder how i survived but truth is i just thought that's what life was about. i was accustomed to survival from a very young age so even the struggles after the original trauma just seemed like normal life. i'm nearly 46 and i'm only learning of my cptsd in the past few years. it's so refreshing to understand that i'm not just crazy that my brain has conditioned me to fight or flight responses.  ox never be afraid to speak up and ask for help. you are honestly never alone. so many people suffer in silence and there is no need xo
love and light xoxox hope you all have a very merry xmas and safe happy new year xoxox

text: bang fringe? nope! my stress related hair loss regrowth is at the “perfect” place to look like i’m attempting some banging bangs. horrible pun 🤪 you know, sometimes i look at this visual reminder of my sexual assault and it makes me angry. angry that someone abused my trust, leveraged his authority and took something from me without my consent. and now i’m left with this unwelcome hair flap that is also curlier than the rest of my hair so when my hair is parted on the other side, it looks like ponytail breakage. but, it has grown and will continue to, just like me. interesting fact: stress related hair loss usually occurs about three months after the traumatic event. i didn’t expect the hair loss to begin that long afterwards but it was the catalyst that got me into much needed counseling. #metoo #metoomovement #sexualassault #normalizementalhealth #counseling #bangfringe #hairloss #justkeepgrowing

text:
【 大叔的愛奪日本十大流行語 】

到底bl劇《大叔的愛》有幾紅？只要去一轉旺角信和中心地庫專賣日本雜誌的舖頭逛逛就知道了，那些封面人物，十之有九都是「春田田」田中圭大頭相，還未計他奪得《gq japan》「men of the year」、《大叔的愛》寫真集在日本賣出10萬冊、他與「黑澤部長」吉田鋼太郎奪得「2018東京劇集大獎」視帝和最佳男配角、劇集落實開拍電影版、田中圭主演的abema tv網上節目《田中圭24小時電視 —— 唇上wanted》總觀看人數達350萬⋯⋯真係講唔完，月初又增添一項 —— 《大叔的愛》日文「おっさんずラブ」勇奪「2018日本流行語top 10」。 年度大獎是「そだねー」（是這樣），這是年初出戰平昌冬奧的日本女子冰壺項目「ls北見隊」隊員於比賽中經常使用的詞語。「そだねー」據説是北海道方言，與標準日語的發音稍有不同，她們在平昌冬奧會摘銅，是日本在冰壺史上的首枚奧運會獎牌，眾隊員的神勇表現和燦爛笑容感染民眾，令「そだねー」成為年度流行語。

至於《大叔的愛》，雖然只是7集的深夜劇，收視不高卻人氣爆燈，最後兩集播出的時候，「#おっさんずラブ」連續兩周成為twitter熱門搜尋榜第一位，成為「年度流行語」當之無愧。其餘8個潮語分別是：（1）eスポーツ 電競、（2）半端ないって（不簡單）：誇獎日本足球國家隊選手大迫勇在比賽中表現出色、（3）ご飯論法（米飯辯論法）：日本國會上經常出現、一種轉移論點的辯論方法。（4）災害級の暑さ（災害級酷熱天氣）、（5）スーパーボランティア（超級志願者）：大分縣的78歲前魚店老闆尾畠春夫於今年8月自告奮勇前往山口縣參與兩歲男孩的搜救行動。 （6）奈良判定：日本拳擊聯盟前會長山根明因涉嫌干涉裁判和獎金分配不公等引發的一系列問題；（7）ボーと生きてんじゃねえよ！（不要迷迷糊糊地活着！）：出自nhk電視節目《知子醬開罵！》（チコちゃんに叱られる！）由cg合成的5歲「毒舌」小女孩，經常出其不意地向大人提出平時不會注意的簡單問題，如果嘉賓答不上來就會被知子罵：「不要迷迷糊糊地活着！」（8）#metoo：不止美國，2018年春天，日本亦曾出現「#metoo運動」，事緣當時日本財務省次官福田淳一，被指性騷擾朝日電視台的女記者，事件曝光初期福田一直否認，惟記者有錄音作實，最終福田淳一引咎辭職。

資料來源：日經新聞網 （22122018）

至於《大叔的愛》，雖然只是7集的深夜劇，收視不高卻人氣爆燈，最後兩集播出的時候，「 電競、（2）半端ないって（不簡單）：誇獎日本足球國家隊選手大迫勇在比賽中表現出色、（3）ご飯論法（米飯辯論法）：日本國會上經常出現、一種轉移論點的辯論方法。（4）災害級の暑さ（災害級酷熱天氣）、（5）スーパーボランティア（超級志願者）：大分縣的78歲前魚店老闆尾畠春夫於今年8月自告奮勇前往山口縣參與兩歲男孩的搜救行動。 （6）奈良判定：日本拳擊聯盟前會長山根明因涉嫌干涉裁判和獎金分配不公等引發的一系列問題；（7）ボーと生きてんじゃねえよ！（不要迷迷糊糊地活着！）：出自nhk電視節目《知子醬開罵！》（チコちゃんに叱られる！）由cg合成的5歲「毒舌」小女孩，經常出其不意地向大人提出平時不會注意的簡單問題，如果嘉賓答不上來就會被知子罵：「不要迷迷糊糊地活着！」（8）etoo：不止美國，2018年春天，日本亦曾出現「etoo運動」，事緣當時日本財務省次官福田淳一，被指性騷擾朝日電視台的女記者，事件曝光初期福田一直否認，惟記者有錄音作實，最終福田淳一引咎辭職。

資料來源：日經新聞網 （22122018）

text:
2018 - for et år; it was the best of times, it was the worst of times.
i våres ble jeg spurt i en paneldebatt hva som har overrasket meg mest siste år. mitt svar var hvor provoserende det fremdeles er å snakke om likestilling i enkelte mannsdominerte miljøer. siden har en annen ting overrasket meg mer: hvor kraftige reaksjoner man får når man sier fra om åpenbar trakassering, maktmisbruk og seksuell trakassering ved norske sykehus. derfor har så langt nesten ingen leger sagt fra. i høst publiserte tidsskriftet en undersøkelse som viser at 22% av norske kvinnelige leger har opplevd seksuell trakassering. det er 4 ganger så mange som snittet i norsk arbeidsliv. hvorfor er tallene så mye høyere i sykehusvesenet? fordi sykehusene er rigget for maktmisbruk.
i våres gikk jeg mange runder med meg selv om jeg skulle si fra eller ikke. jeg hadde opplevd og sett andre oppleve situasjoner som ikke er greit, og som til dels ikke er lovlig. likevel var det ingen konsekvenser eller reaksjoner fra sykehuset. det er den letteste og den vanskeligste avgjørelsen jeg har tatt. lett fordi noen må si fra. vanskelig fordi jeg skjønte hva jeg risikerte ved å gjøre det. men nettopp når man har noe å tape, er det viktig å si fra. det viktigste maktmiddelet som har ligget i sykehusene er manglende transparens, og trusler om sanksjoner hvis man sier fra. og definitivt gjennomføring av sanksjonene mot leger som poengterer forhold som på ingen måte er innafor. derfor valgte jeg å si fra. ikke fordi jeg er "oppmerksomhetssyk" som jeg siden fikk høre fra noen i ledelsen.
resten er historie, men historien har nok artet seg langt mer utmattende på innsiden enn den tilsynelatende har sett ut fra utsiden.
det positive er at vi fra toppen av helsevesenet ser en vilje til endring. tanara burke, grunnleggeren av #metoo, har sagt "movements activate possibilities." det sies at troll sprekker i lyset. i 2019 skal jeg gjøre det jeg kan for å sørge for at sykehusvesenet orienterer seg for tid og sted. sammen med en veldig samlet assistentlegetropp. tusen, tusen takk for all støtte og kjærlighet fra kjent og ukjente assistentleger og overleger over hele landet! foto henrik shek, ylf.
name: Marie Louise Sunde

i våres ble jeg spu i en paneldebatt hva som har overrasket meg mest siste år. mitt svar var hvor provoserende det fremdeles er å snakke om likestilling i enkelte mannsdominee miljøer. siden har en annen ting overrasket meg mer: hvor kraftige reaksjoner man får når man sier fra om åpenbar trakassering, maktmisbruk og seksuell trakassering ved norske sykehus. derfor har så langt nesten ingen leger sagt fra. i høst publisee tidsskriftet en undersøkelse som viser at 22% av norske kvinnelige leger har opplevd seksuell trakassering. det er 4 ganger så mange som snittet i norsk arbeidsliv. hvorfor er tallene så mye høyere i sykehusvesenet? fordi sykehusene er rigget for maktmisbruk.
i våres gikk jeg mange runder med meg selv om jeg skulle si fra eller ikke. jeg hadde opplevd og sett andre oppleve situasjoner som ikke er greit, og som til dels ikke er lovlig. likevel var det ingen konsekvenser eller reaksjoner fra sykehuset. det er den letteste og den vanskeligste avgjørelsen jeg har tatt. lett fordi noen må si fra. vanskelig fordi jeg skjønte hva jeg risikee ved å gjøre det. men nettopp når man har noe å tape, er det viktig å si fra. det viktigste maktmiddelet som har ligget i sykehusene er manglende transparens, og trusler om sanksjoner hvis man sier fra. og definitivt gjennomføring av sanksjonene mot leger som poengterer forhold som på ingen måte er innafor. derfor valgte jeg å si fra. ikke fordi jeg er "oppmerksomhetssyk" som jeg siden fikk høre fra noen i ledelsen.
resten er historie, men historien har nok aet seg langt mer utmattende på innsiden enn den tilsynelatende har sett ut fra utsiden.
det positive er at vi fra toppen av helsevesenet ser en vilje til endring. tanara burke, grunnleggeren av  har sagt "movements activate possibilities." det sies at troll sprekker i lyset. i 2019 skal jeg gjøre det jeg kan for å sørge for at sykehusvesenet orienterer seg for tid og sted. sammen med en veldig samlet assistentlegetropp. tusen, tusen takk for all støtte og kjærlighet fra kjent og ukjente assistentleger og overleger over hele landet! foto henrik shek, ylf.

text:
2018 has been a bitch.
i don't want to hold this speech as deep as a plot to an amature gay porn but.. i got to know so many people and also my career has improved through events like one when guns n roses shared my cover from their song estranged. it was a crazy feeling to know that people see something unique in you and want to spread the word. i am also grateful for my friends who helped me through hard times including through the time karl logan sexually harassed me via facebook and skype when i was 17. it has been a challenge for me but i was strong enough to fight against it. also this year i had my first partymonium in may and it was amazing to see all of my glam rock maniacs and party with them like it was 1985.
it was like a birthday party for me because my 18th birthday was may the 15th. also this year i got my driving license and my first car and had my first job going on, so many events. i am more grateful to have parents who support me in life and also entertain me with going to concerts with me like for example i went to see guns n roses with my dad this year. love him for that. i don't take their support for granted and so i don't take my friends' support for granted. i appreciate every single second with them. thanks for saving my year and made it a good one. 😊 🖤 sending love

text: i'm sitting here with tears in my brown eyes and a mind and heart trying to write this tribute to you sisters who still walk this beautiful, horrible world. i want all of you to understand why my tear-stained shirt a hurting sister was forced to sew me is still sticking to my clean and soiled and hydrated and dry skin. i'm trying to tell you why, since this dim sepia-ish photo was taken by one of my strong mamas on one of the most dazzling days of my life, i've metaphorically-and-literally-littered empty cardboard boxes, thin cotton cheap tees and sweaters, and countless pounds of tears and toxins from a strong and broken body. my eyes are tired because since this photo of me and two of my freshly-reborn sisters was taken, i've been humbled, favored, blessed and cursed to traverse a few more feet of this horrid and beautiful world. to still walk til my perfectly designed yet still imperfect, hurting body stops exuding passionate and exhausted life. i'm remembering why my heart that my big sister told me is like a fragile tiffany lamp got broken, again. i'm remembering  the week that made me tired in the best and worst ways i've lived. it was 8 days ago that all my mamas and all my big and fraternal twin and baby sisters told me they were honored hear me recite some of the book of my life. but after all my moms wrapped their arms right around me, held me next to their beautiful broken beating hearts, and cheered me on, i'm still aching for another warm hug from a perfect whole beating strong heart.  because i opened my eyes again, outside the walls of a safe, grace-filled home, and shut them tight.  and i can catch up on the news, but it would burn me like that bright sun and break my heart again. because i know far too many sisters of mine out there have been destroyed while i somehow received grace to be loved and tenderly rebuilt. to those sisters: you are the why behind @sistersandheroes. i can't save you, but i can hope to raise my voice and paintbrush so you will not be a #metoo. so you can always say no. so you can be fully you. this is for you- you can. i'll see you on the other side.

text:
it’s been a hard couple of weeks for so many of the women in my life, for so many people i love, for me. i did what i always do when i’m trying to heal: i wrote. here’s some of it: “i am woman
all curves before age
i feel venus in the back of my throat as lyrics drip from lips on streets in ways that molest the most sacred parts of my body 
as fingers and hands grab in ways that never 
respected anything they caught
i am an object
less than human
only a woman
no words, no stories, no alibis 
no tears, no bruised bones 
she will never ever be enough
i wish i can wrap my arms around the beautiful black and brown bodies of my sisters
i want to slowly kiss away the bruises inside their gorgeous hearts
melting away the etched memories of wandering misogynist fingers and masculine sounds 
i want to wrap my baby sister in pre colonial matriarchy and femininity and self love and safety 
i just want her to be safe. 
before her eyes teach her to hate what she finds in the mirror
to seek affirmation in boys that never learned to love themselves
i wish i can heal myself”

text:
@regrann from @agathaa.writes - * this post will be in hindi and english *
...
as girls, we all have gone through at least one situation where we have to prove-
arey bhai hum ladkiyan kum nahi hain. where we need to remind people and society, that before being a girl, i'm a human. ladki hona hota hai, ghar pe baithke yeh sikhna ki khana kaise banate hain? kapde kaise dhote hain?  ya shaadi kaise karte hain? 
if you think a girl is brought to this vast planet consisting billions of population, to serve one man at the stake of her own passion and dreams, then i would feel no shame in telling that you need to have a glass of wine and get a life. 
and the important thing is, kindly stop telling your daughters,  wives, mothers, sisters, girlfriends - basically your girls how they need to talk and sit and walk. and there's this one phase i am sure every girl reading this right now have faced. the stalker. 
i mean. stalk koi banda kar raha hai. pareshan vo banda kar raha hai. haddhein usse pata honi chahiye. par restrictions kispe lagte hain? you don't have to upload any of your photo. 
the most common reaction is-
why are you even on social media??? okay, so you mean just so that such assholes don't find a route to bother me, i should socially just isolate myself? so basically it's like. ladka jo karta hai karne do, tum chup rehkar baitho. i simply ask. why? uss stalker ne aisa kaunsa amrit ka pyaala piya hai jo uske liye hum chup rahein? he isn't a ruler. and i am not his subject. so stop teaching your girls how to accept defeat. tell them what a freaking power they are. make them realize that they are living in 21st century and they have the right to expression. 
and ek cheez jo mujhe abhi tak samajh nahi aayi. i have come across many people here. and most of them are influencers. either writers,  bloggers,  painters, artists, singers. you know, some kind of artists. and i really don't understand ki how does my face, my identity, my 'so-called beauty' is going to affect my art? man, i write that means i write.(-continued in comments-)

text:
الصحفيون اختاروا أسوأ الأشخاص في عام ٢٠١٨
٢٠١٨ كانت سنة مليئة بالقضايا الجدلية في صناعة الترفيه الكوري، والآن بما أنه لم يتبقى شيء على ختام السنة لخّص الصحفيون من صحيفة sports today أسوأ الأشخاص بأسوأ القضايا الجدلية في ٢٠١٨.

تفقدوا القائمة أدناه لمعرفة أسوأ الأشخاص وفقا لاختيار الصحفيين.

يانغ هيون سوك: إلغاء ترسيم “ميكس ناين”
قال الصحفي يون هاي يونغ: “بالقوة التي تملكها وكالة yg، هو قال بأن الترسيم سيحدث ووضع المتدربين في منافسة فيما بينهم، لكنه ألغى ترسيمهم لأن البرنامج فشل. هو أثار جدل برده على اجراءاتهم القانونية بدعوى قضائية مضادة. ومن ثم أطلق برنامج تنافسي جديد مشابه لـ “ميكس ناين” على الرغم من أنه لم تمضي سنة كاملة حتى على انتهاء “ميكس ناين”. أفكاره الساخرة تصدم الجميع”. لي سيو وون: تحرش جنسي
قال الصحفي كيم سات بيول: “تصرفه الجريء بعد قضية التحرش الجنسي، وجهله المستمر، وأخيرا، هروبه من كل شيء بالتحاقه بالجيش. لقد صُدمت لثلاث مرات”. كيم سانغ مين: حركة #metoo
قال الصحفي كيم نا يون: “هو دمّر وقته الذهبي الذي طال انتظاره منذ ٢٥ عاما. أنت تحصد ما تزرعه”. نانسي لانغ x وانغ: زواج وطلاق جدلي
قال الصحفي هان يي جي: “مثيران للمشاكل بزواجهما الإشكالي، وشجاراهتما، ومن ثم طلاقهما”. المقدمة لي جين مين: تلاعب بـ heart signal 2
قال الصحفي مون سو يون: “هي أنشأت البرنامج الشهير heart signal لكن كان هناك أيضا العديد من القضايا الجدلية. هي خيّبت أمل المشاهدين أكثر بسلوكها الغاضب في مقابلة أجريت معها عن أخطاء البث، والتلاعب في التحرير، والمزيد”. الرابر ميكرودوت: احتيال والديه
قال الصحفي كيم هيون مين: “والديه كذبا على أهل مدينتهم، والابن كذب على المشاهدين”.

text:
#voguepeople100
2018年即將畫下尾聲，時尚圈與娛樂圈的明星們持續運用其影響力渲染著全球各地的人們。

回顧今年，英國王妃梅根馬克爾 #meghanmarkle  使出超狂的「梅根同款」效應；在流量為王的數位浪潮下，西方的卡達夏珍娜家族、蕾哈娜 @badgalriri #rihanna 繼續霸佔社群媒體頭條，賺起「網紅經濟」

而東方一線流量小生與花旦 #吳亦凡 和 #楊冪 則成為千禧世代的「帶貨力」保證；提前新登場的「z世代」促使時尚精品做出更年輕化的策略

@chanelofficial #chanel 祭出 #lilyrosedepp @lilyrose_depp 與日本國民女兒 #木村光希 #koki 搶先聽牌；#metoo 運動掀起骨牌效應，兩大dior代言人 #jenniferlawrence 與 #natalieportman 搖著女權主義的旗幟，串起全球各地性別平權與反性騷擾的意識；碧昂絲 @beyonce 制霸coachella音樂盛典展現黑人的歷史與驕傲，翻越種族藩籬展開平等對話。

text:
to: built up emotions

i didn't want to to rock the boat

tip the thought

hear the gawk about

that

i didn't want to

see the clear 
view the mirror

reflecting back 
those truths

hitting home

beating deep

in my chest

i didn't want to wipe 
the floor

of the mess

leave it there

for the next

i didn't want that thing called pressure

to burst over

but it did

#underpressure#emotions#emotional#emotionpoetry#thepoem

text: the worst feeling in the world is feeling completely alone in a room full of people, family members, your husband, friends... because no one has taken the time to understand you, to understand what you’re feeling, what you’re going through. no one has held space for you. you don’t feel heard or like your feelings or opinions matter. you’re made to feel incapable, small... an individual is only able to handle so much until they break, until they have had enough. if you have a loved one dealing with mental illness, bi-polar, an eating disorder, ptsd, etc... i urge you to educate yourself on what they’re going through, read up on it before you make judgments. show your love by putting the effort in to try and understand. because comments like “you just need to move past it” “you can’t let it get to you” those are things that don’t help. educate yourself. #alone #anxiety #depression #mentalhealth #mentalhealthawareness #educateyourself #metoo #iamnotsmall #thinkbeforeyouspeak #dontjudge #myopinionsmatter #myfeelingsmatter

while her story may not be that recent, it’s important nonetheless. cyntoia brown was only 16 when she was convicted of first-degree murder, and given a 51 year sentence without parole. brown was a victim of sex trafficking, who was sold to a man named johnny allen. she claimed that the pimp that sold her threatened her repeatedly with guns in his house, and she was afraid he would kill her, so when he told her to “go make money”, she found johnny allen to have sex with (her confession is on slide four). she is a victim that was failed by the justice system! here’s how you can help her or show her some love:⁣
⁣
call governor bill halsam’s line on her behalf! he can grant clemency. his number is:⁣
⁣
(615)741-2001⁣
⁣
or, email him at:⁣
⁣
bill.haslam@tn.gov⁣
⁣
write to her! show her you support and are seeking justice! here’s how to reach her:⁣
⁣
ms cyntoia d brown #410593⁣
⁣
tennessee prison for women⁣
⁣
2 north, b49⁣
⁣
3881 stewarts lane⁣
⁣
nashville, tn 37218⁣
⁣

📸 tag a fellow feminist who should read this! 📸

happy feminist friday y’all. the color purple is a classic. with over a million copies sold in the uk alone, it is hailed as one of the all-time ‘greats’ of literature, inspiring generations of readers.

set in the deep american south between the wars, it is the tale of celie, a young black girl born into poverty and segregation. raped repeatedly by the man she calls ‘father’, she has two children taken away from her, is separated from her beloved sister nettie and is trapped into an ugly marriage. but then she meets the glamorous shug avery, singer and magic-maker - a woman who has taken charge of her own destiny. gradually, celie discovers the power and joy of her own spirit, freeing her from her past and reuniting her with those she loves.

text:
eliza dushku has broken her silence in a powerful op-ed for the boston globe to repudiate what she describes as “revisionist accounts” put forth by cbs and former co-star michael weatherly, whom she accused of sexual harassment. cbs paid the actress a $9.5 million settlement, which was disclosed in a new york times report last week, to ensure her silence after she appeared for three episodes on the legal drama “bull”. she alleges series star weatherly made “cruel” and “aggressive” jokes about sex, rape and her appearance in front of cast and crew members. 
dushku rejects the notion that her grievances arose from a misunderstanding between herself and weatherly, who apologized in a statement to the times, saying he was “mortified” his sense of humor misfired. dushku, meanwhile, declined to comment in the bombshell report due to the conditions of the settlement. however, after weatherly and cbs did respond to the times, dushku says in wednesday’s op-ed, she decided to speak out. “i grew up in boston with three elder brothers and have generally been considered a tomboy. i made a name for myself playing a badass vampire slayer turned toughla cheerleader,” dushku writes. “i do not want to hear that i have a ‘humor deficit’ or can’t take a joke. i did not over-react. i took a job and, because i did not want to be harassed, i was fired.” . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . .  #elizadushku #equality #feminism #feminist #feminists #timesup #metoo #metoomovement #yesallwomen #fuckthepatriarchy  #smashthepatriarchy #yesallwomen #sexualharassment #harassment #sexualassault #feminism_around_the_world
name: feminism around the world

text:
last year we set out to create a series of ads to protest the practice of victim-blaming as a tool to excuse sexual assault. a phenomenal team of film-makers came together to help us, and the campaign came alive. it spread virally around the globe, was covered by media worldwide, and launched thousands of online conversations in a dizzying array of languages.

the response was overwhelming — it was beyond gratifying to know that our little project could have such an impact on attitudes, and maybe even (hopefully) on actual behaviors.

and while we know that awards can’t compare when measured against real-world results, we appreciate the industry recognition nonetheless. thank you @communicationarts for including us in the 2018 advertising annual! —————————————#metoo #itstime #fff #itsonus #nomeansno #womensmarch

we’ve started this blog in hopes of educating people everywhere. we’ve decided to speak out on a variety of global issues such as gender equality, animal rights, rape culture, mental illnesses, youth rights, etc. our goal is to fight for the equality for everyone no matter your race, age, gender, or orientation, and empowering you all to join this fight; we can’t do this alone! follow us, and subscribe to our blog to stay updated! we can’t wait for you to read what we have ready for you all!

after all, that is the essence of equality.

•••
“a dress code’s purpose is to provide guidance to students and parents as to what appropriate attire is for school and at any school function and ensure a “distraction-free”, learning environment for everyone but it has slowly turned into yet another way to oppress women. why is the dress code mainly applicable to females? why are the females pulled out of class, and told her clothes are “inappropriate”? why must females education be placed at a lower level than the males?” ~ musk

text:
swipee ➡️➡️ {photo creds: @the_indian_feminist }
“the normalization of rape: rape culture” ••• “rape culture. when it’s mentioned, stories of sexual assault and abuse come forward, causing awkward silences and discomfort. why does the mention of rape culture make us uncomfortable, but not the physical action of forcing yourself onto someone? we collectively agree that rape is wrong but hesitate when speaking of rape culture, often because the meaning is misunderstood. it’s scary to think that our actions could ever contribute to rape. until we put a stop to actions that normalize, and excuse rape, it will never be fully dealt with. “ ~ musk

text:
hace unos días leí una noticia que decía que habían asesinado a dos chicas escandinavas a unos pocos kilómetros de unos de los lugares que visitamos en marruecos el mes pasado. si bien es un caso excepcional porque es un país que recibe millones de turistas y no es que todos los días vemos estas noticias, debo decir que en mi experiencia fue uno de los países donde me sentí más incómodo. no me sentí inseguro como en muchos lugares de latinoamérica pero me sentí siempre a la defensiva porque todos me querían estafar todo el tiempo. fue un país muy agotador. no volvería, al menos no en el corto plazo. muchos instagrammers lo pusieron de moda porque se quedan en riads de miles de dólares la noche o van al desierto pero la realidad del día a día en el país es muy diferente. y yo fui en pareja. para mujeres solas es un destino que no recomiendo. si bien, tristemente, viajar como mujer sola nunca es lo mismo que viajar como siendo hombre, hay países donde es más fácil que otros. de todos los países que conozco hasta ahora, me animo a decir que marruecos es el peor para mujeres solas.
lo qué pasó es terrible, lo qué pasa es terrible. de verdad que no lo puedo entender. no creo que sea una cuestión religiosa porque hoy en día está claro qué pasa en todo el mundo. es más una cuestión cultural y va a llevar años cambiar pero se está entendiendo un poco más el tema gracias a mujeres increíbles que están empezando a levantar la voz. ojalá más lo hagan y ojalá más hombres vayan entendiendo que lo que hacen no está bien. no hace falta llegar a la agresión física para cruzar la línea, la mayor cantidad de transgresiones son verbales o miradas que muchas veces se han naturalizado pero que están mal. está mal.
.
.
.
.
.
.
#metoo #sevaacaer #marruecos #sunsetbeach #sunsetlover #birdsofinstagram #mujeresviajeras #viajeras #argentina

text:
russell simmons demands $10 million rape lawsuit be tossed, highlights support of me too movement in his defense - blogged by @msjennyb
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
russell simmons has officially responded in the $10 million rape lawsuit filed against him, and he’s using his support of the “metoo" movement in his defense to get the case dismissed. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
in documents filed on december 20 and obtained by the blast, simmons detailed his work history as a well-known entrepreneur and civil rights activist who “fully embraces the #metoo movement” and the importance of “creating safe spaces for women to thrive and lead in every facet of our society.” ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
“with every great revolution there has been collateral damage,” simmons said in his response. “in this movement, this includes mr. simmons’ well-publicized life as a celebrity bachelor being the target of outrageous false tabloid-fodder allegations contradicted by facts and the law.” ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
in the initial suit, doe accused simmons of rape back in 1988, claiming the media mogul forced himself on her after threatening to rape her adolescent son. but, in simmons’ response, he says the suit is just part of doe’s plan to extort the mogul with the false accusations. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
as a result, simmons is demanding the case be tossed for good.

text:
red door, black door - watercolor - 21 x 29 inches

every morning, the queen of north beach walks her panther. here they are on fresno street. in san francisco it is illegal to walk your pets without a leash. you have to look closely to see that the panther’s leash is only a ribbon that the queen chose to match the color of her dress and parasol.

she told me that one morning a policeman stopped her to warn her that a ribbon was not a real leash. “it was just an excuse,” she said, “to ask me for my phone number.” “did you give it to him?” “i gave him a smile.” #art #landscapeart #artforsale #modernart #metoo #fineart #contemporaryart #realistart #visualpoetry #artlovers  #visionaryart #surrealistart

text:
para reporter memilih 6 kontroversi paling buruk sepanjang tahun 2018

2018 adalah tahun dengan berbagai skandal di k-entertainment dengan banyak masalah kontroversial, tuntutan hukum, dan banyak lagi. sekarang dengan hanya beberapa minggu tersisa di tahun ini, wartawan dari sports today menyimpulkan orang-orang terburuk dengan kontroversi terburuk pada tahun 2018. siapa yang menurut para wartawan adalah yang terburuk tahun ini? lihatlah daftar di bawah ini:

1. yang hyun suk: pembatalan debut 'mixnine' "dengan kekuatan yg sebagai agensi, dia mengatakan dia akan membuat debut dan menempatkan peserta pelatihan dalam kompetisi, tetapi membatalkan debut mereka karena program itu gagal. dia menciptakan kontroversi dengan menanggapi geliat terakhir mereka mengambil tindakan hukum dengan gugatan balik. kemudian bahkan setahun kemudian, dia menciptakan acara audisi yang sama 'yg treasure box.' ide ironisnya mengejutkan semua orang. " - reporter yoon hye young.

2. lee seo won: pelecehan seksual "tingkah lakunya yang berani setelah pelecehan seksual, ketidaktahuan terus-menerus, dan terakhir, tindakan melarikan diri ke militer. aku terkejut 3 kali." - reporter kim sat byul

3. kim saeng min: #metoo "dia menghabiskan waktu emas yang ditunggu-tunggu dalam 25 tahun. kamu mendapatkan apa yang kamu berikan." - reporter kim na yeon

4. nancy lang x wang: pernikahan dan perceraian yang kontroversial "pembuat masalah dengan perkawinan, perkelahian, dan perceraian yang gaduh." - reporter han ye ji

5. lee jin min cp: manipulasi 'heart signal 2' "dia menciptakan program viral 'heart signal' tetapi ada juga banyak kontroversi. dia bahkan lebih mengecewakan penonton dengan perilakunya yang tidak menyenangkan dalam wawancara tentang kesalahan siaran, manipulasi dalam penyuntingan, dan banyak lagi." - reporter moon soo yeon

6. microdot: kasus lenipuan orang tua "orang tuanya berbohong kepada orang-orang di kota mereka, putranya berbohong kepada pemirsa." - reporter kim hyun min

source : allkpop, oh_mes
trans by : pink
©ksense

text:
info • repórteres escolhem as piores controvérsias de 2018.
.
2018 foi um ano escandaloso para o k-pop, com muitos assuntos controvérsios, ações judiciais e muito mais. agora com apenas algumas semanas para o fim do ano, os repórteres da sports today escolheram as piores pessoas com as piores controvérsias em 2018.
.
confira:
.
1. yang hyun suk: cancelamento do mixnine.
.
"com o poder da yg como base, ele disse que faria a estreia e colocaria os vencedores em ação, mas cancelou o debut porque o programa fracassou. ele criou uma controvérsia ao responder à sua última tentativa de tomar medidas legais com um processo. então, nem em menos de um ano depois, ele criou um programa similar 'yg treasure box'. sua ideia irônica choca todo mundo".
.
2. lee seowon: abuso sexual.
.
"seu comportamento ousado após o assédio sexual, ignorância e o ato de fugir de seus depoimentos causaram isso."
.
3. kim saeng min: #metoo
.
"ele desperdiçou seu tão esperado tempo de ouro em 25 anos. você colhe o que planta."
.
4. nancy lang x wang: casamento conturbado.
.
"fabricantes de problemas no casamento, divórcios e separações."
.
5. lee jin min: manipulação no heart signal 2. .
"ela criou o programa viral 'heart signal', mas também houve muitas controvérsias. ela desapontou ainda mais os espectadores com seu comportamento desagradável na entrevista sobre erros de transmissão, manipulação na edição e muito mais."
.
6. microdot: fraude dos pais.
.
"os pais mentiram para as pessoas, o filho mentiu para os telespectadores". .
tr/pt: k-pop news
não retirar sem os devidos créditos.

text:
#جنتی
مگه میشه مگه داریم یعنی یک قرن عمر کرده گاف نداده من که گشتم هیچی پیدا نکردم. شش یک از چرچیل هم جلو هست.
شاید برای همه جالب باشه تو این #گاو_دکفته_بازار و‌فسادی که رخنه کرده و افسار گسیخته شده و کنترلش از دست  آقایان خارج شده چون صد البته پای همه گیره تنها مسی که ازش حرفی نیست همین گل پسر #جنتی هست .البته فتوا و قل قمع یای سیاسی ایشان در سمت شورای نگهبان را کنار بگذاریم بحث مالی را می گویم . برای منم هم جالبه 
اکثر برنامه های صدای آمریکا از فلاحتی تا چالنگی و نوری زاد تا منو تو و بی بی سی تو زمانی که اختلاص های آقا و آقا زاده ها را رو می کردند هیچ سند و حرفی از این بابا نزدند البته واسه منم جالب هست .
ای قشنگ تر از خیلی ها می می خوای بری 
پیر مرد با مزه ای هیچ وقت هم بازنشست نمیشه به قول #محسن_رفیقدوست که از چهار نفر اصلی و حلقه اصلی رهبری هست آنهایی که حقوق نمیگیرند بازنشست هم نمیشن
#شبکه_نیم #یلدا #گاو_دکفته_بازار #دولت_بهار #دولت_تدبیر #دولت_روحانی #نگهبان#metoo #iranintl #manotoeslahat#اصلاحات#نمایندگان#گیلان #رشتیها

text: i had to change my number because the harassment wouldn’t stop. calls from unidentified numbers inquiring on the well being of my teenage little girl jolted me into a deeper depression. how could i have not seen the signs. why did i do this to my family. why couldn’t i be perfect, smart and have enough self love to know that this was all a cruel game. no one is perfect but no one deserves to be preyed upon, mislead and humiliated to near nothing. the games predators, narcissist and broken vessels play are not to be taken lightly, their mindset can be deadly but the protection of my god was bigger than any game. i’ve been quiet long enough, my eyes are wide open to this world no more sheltered thinking it almost cost my family too much.  the stories i’ve encountered over the past year have shook me to my core. my own story was enough to see i needed help, selflove and a wake up call. this one area in my life “ relationship “ almost cost me my sanity and well being of my child. enough is enough, mental health has got to be the route. #voice #fightback #truth #wontgiveuop #mentalhealth #selflove #mentalhealthawareness #mentalhealth #speak  #women #sexoffender #warriors #fallible #sunroom #lovequotes #selflove #minister #ministry #purpose #purposedrivenlife  #god #hypebeast #fashionista #trump #golden #yellow #redtabletalk #womenspeakers #metoo #rosearmy #voice

it happens every day and it's never okay, it shouldn't be a norm.

text:
today’s a big day of memories for me. 7 yrs ago today, i got engaged. i could say it was a happy time back then...but honestly even that day wasn’t happy. i spent a portion of it crying, upset, didn’t think my feelings were being considered. and yes, i was being hella dramatic. i literally put a fake engagement ring on &showed it to my boyfriend &told him i needed to wear it out because we had been dating for 6.5 years &it was long overdo. who’s dis crazy bitch? 🤪😂 (for the record, i did not wear it out. 😂😂)
.
little did i know, he’d be proposing later that night...and when it happened, i thought i was happy. this is what i had been waiting for! after so long together it was clearly the next step, right?
.
but what i wasn’t thinking about that day was the time he wouldn’t even look at me on my birthday, because he didn’t like what i was wearing. or when he told me no one likes me because i always try to one-up people (i’m pretty honest about my flaws, but that is not one of them...however it was one of his #gaslighting). or when he would get jealous and act crazy when i talked to other guys. and when he felt challenged by those guys and said, “he can have you”...as if i was a prize to be won. i’m ashamed to say all these things happened, and still i stayed.
.
real talk: in an emotionally abusive relationship, it’s easy to say, “it wasn’t my fault”, and that’s absolutely true. but here’s the part i do have to own up to...
.
i allowed it. .
my lack of boundaries invited him to disrespect me. it’s like an enemy army rushing into a city and all of the soldiers are asleep instead of standing at the gate ready to protect their homes!
.
that part was my responsibility, and my own insecurities kept me from doing it well. it was something i’d have to change if i ever wanted to move forward and heal. and i did.
.
so with this negative memory today, i thought i’d make a better one - stay tuned for that announcement soon! .
if you made it this far, thank you for allowing me to share a snippet of my story. my hope is that by baring my soul, i can help even one girl to avoid what i did and realize she is worth so much more!❤️

text:
january 22, 2018 i had made a decision to “get out”. it was surprisingly the hardest yet easiest decision i have actually ever made in this life. i left an abusive relationship to learn more about love. i left a toxic relationship to build a stronger personal one with myself. i left a man to learn who i was needing to become as a woman. 
i left. i took very little. i took my babies. i cried. a lot. i struggled to get on my feet. i struggled to pay my bills. i was homeless for 4 months. i fought for a fair custody. i fought for a fair child support. i fought. and i continue to fight. 
i have learned that people will not approve of who you want to become based off of who you were. loving myself this year wasn’t really a priority. i hated myself. i gained weight. i had tried to end my life a few times. i had fallen into a deep depression. i was living a stressed out, high anxiety, hateful life. and let me tell you something last night i had one of the most incredible evenings this year. 
i had a funeral for my failed relationship. i had a birthday celebration of my rebirth. today i woke up feeling a since of acceptance. my best friends surrounded me last night with love, laughter and their friendship.

thank you ladies for helping me celebrate a new beginning of this life. may the journey of self discovery and healing continue. 
#teamhalfbreed #70sinspired #rebirth #funeral #fuckdepression #anxiety #mentalhealthisreal #mentalhealth #battlingabattlenoonesees #behindasmile #metoo

text:
🧟‍♀️locura de fin de año🧟‍♀️ es diciembre y el mundo acelera y enloquece (😱). la #medusa de #caravaggio ilustra perfecto el vértigo de este 2018 que se va y el 2019 que vendrá, pero a mi me recuerda al artículo que leí hace poco en @sleekmag y me encantó 💖
.
✍🏼 @emilyjaynemay96 arranca con un statement: en el arte y la literatura, #medusa siempre fue villana 😈 pero la historia detrás del monstruo que convertía en piedra 🗿a todo aquel que se animase a mirarla 👀 era en realidad la de una mujer violada, castigada y decapitada. ¿por qué entonces no retratarla como víctima? porque “se lo había ganado sola” (🙄) gracias a su atractivo físico y poder de seducción.
.
el mito 📜🧖🏻‍♀️ de la belleza peligrosa de #medusa no puede ser más relevante este año después de haber escuchado tantos relatos silenciados de mujeres 🚺 víctimas de violencia, abuso y discriminación de género que salieron a la luz gracias a los movimientos #niunamenos y #metoo. a un paso del #2019 así estamos. todavía locos, despertando de la modorra misógina. el vértigo al cambio es enorme para todos: hombres y mujeres. 👋🏻adiós a los estereotipos, mitos y grandes verdades. mi deseo 🔮 para este año que viene es que aprendamos a convivir en paz, pero sobre todo, en la igualdad de derechos y oportunidades🌎✌🏻

text:
i am excited to announce my second marie claire feature. i am in the january 2019 marie claire issue discussion female genital mutilation and my activism. it is great to reach new audiences and spread the message. my fgm work will have a new home in 2019. i am excited to do my work in a way that is true to my values of integrity, truth, human rights, diversity, inclusion, discrimination free zone, cultural integrity and pride embedded in intersectionality. there is no room for racism, double standards, white saviourism, islamophobia etc. 2018 has been a year of endings, closing chapters, dropping dead weight, cutting off toxic people, removing myself from roles and work spaces that were detrimental to my cultural rights, health, integrity and peace of mind. 2018 has been a year of being assertive and boy was i assertive 😏😇😎. assertive in all areas of my life. here is to 2019 and being true to myself in every way possible and continuing to kickass and be assertive. remember when one door closes another opens.

text:
‪the way girls were raised (day 702)‬
*
*
*

her tiny paper voice redolent of old jewelry 
and longing, decorated with a fairytale ending, 
an act of real-life resistance, saying: “me too! my existence counts as something.” an umbrella, she sheds tears the clouds 
cry for the way girls were raised to run long, 
tapered fingers around wineglass rims, and 
to twirl the tiny paper parasols propped 
atop fruit-laden drinks with titillating names. 
how does she do it—sing songs of such 
encouragement and evocation? yet, there, 
amidst a library of crumbling books in archaic languages, she hums a song so dark and cheerful 
that, in an unlit, unloved corner, goethe stirs 
and blinks approvingly, and she, sensing 
his presence, tosses him a knowing wink. *
*
* (c) 2018, by hannah six

text:
link is on our bio! go to @mattiolipro or @guysatpartieslikeit to get to then kickstarter.

it’s a typical night at the frat house; booze are flowing, boobs are bouncing, and a young frat prodigy, rising through the ranks, is about to get lucky! to score major points with his frat bros and to avoid a humiliating pledge ritual, he leads a wasted sorority girl upstairs to swipe his v-card only to find out, getting lucky isn't as easy as it sounds. "guys at parties like it is a truly disturbing and heartbreaking exploration of the toxic masculinity pervasive in college campuses particularly with fraternity and sorority parties." -wescreenplay competition 
it has been reported that one in four women will experience sexual assault in their lifetime, including rape, molestation, coercion, and date rape. this story depicts the series of unfortunate events that lead to an all too common scenario about a girl, a boy, and the word "no". the #metoo and #timesup campaigns have taken hold of society in what can only be described as this generation's women's lib movement. it's these powerful stories of survival and strength that inspired the screenplay and are reshaping our world.

we understand that rape-revenge films are difficult to watch for a lot of survivors which is why we have decided not to include any graphic rape scenes throughout (but don't worry, there is tons of graphic gore.)
song by sasha velour “pirate jenny” available on youtube

text:
what is life. i am officially a published author. 🖊

truly honored to be a part of this important collection of perspectives on equality & inclusion alongside some incredible asian leaders. ✊🏼 looking back on almost a decade of working in diversity in entertainment, my m nd is blown by how far we’ve come in prioritizing & appreciating real, authentic stories from all walks of life - gender, race, sexuality, geography, generation. even though there’s much more work to do, it’s encouraging to know that these topics matter now more than ever before. and we’re all getting our heads out of the sand to be awake and active in the process. 🧠

i’m continuing to learn just how much representation in entertainment plays out & interacts with every other industry (tech, finance, wellness, etc), including those of my brilliant co-authors. i know these ideas can slip away into just being lofty words or some stuffy soundbites.. but they affect our everyday lives & deserve recognition & our conscious investment. 👥 
equality & inclusion influence the people we serve & the leaders we elect & the many systems that shape our careers, families, & relationships. they are crucial to pursue in any industry & we’ll keep the movement going, one conversation at a time. 🗣

the majority of proceeds from this book will go to the amazing @advancingjustice_aajc. thank you to @chiragdsagar & @askadamtorres for making this happen! find the book on #amazon along with everything else you buy in life. hope its a helpful resource to whoever finds it. 🖊 📸: @thisisge

tweet_full:
what is life. i am officially a published author. 🖊

truly honored to be a part of this important collection of perspectives on equality & inclusion alongside some incredible asian leaders. ✊🏼 looking back on almost a decade of working in diversity in entertainment, my m nd is blown by how far we’ve come in prioritizing & appreciating real, authentic stories from all walks of life - gender, race, sexuality, geography, generation. even though there’s much more work to do, it’s encouraging to know that these topics matter now more than ever before. and we’re all getting our heads out of the sand to be awake and active in the process. 🧠

i’m continuing to learn just how much representation in entertainment plays out & interacts with every other industry (tech, fice, wellness, etc), including those of my brilliant co-authors. i know these ideas can slip away into just being lofty words or some stuffy soundbites.. but they affect our everyday lives & deserve recognition & our conscious investment. 👥 
equality & inclusion influence the people we serve & the leaders we elect & the many systems that shape our careers, families, & relationships. they are crucial to pursue in any industry & we’ll keep the movement going, one conversation at a time. 🗣

the majority of proceeds from this book will go to the amazing @advancingjustice_aajc. thank you to @chiragdsagar & @askadamtorres for making this happen! find the book on #amazon along with everything else you buy in life. hope its a helpful resource to whoever finds it. 🖊 📸: @thisisge

text:
“drowning” a self portrait photo project that is very vulnerable for me. you can read what i wrote & see the rest of the photos in the link on my profile. “drowning” is a very short article and photo series i wrote to portray feelings and moments i have experienced as a sexual assault & abusive relationship survivor with ptsd to bring awareness during the holidays, being that i feel that’s when these issues need light shed on them the most. 
side note, these were all taken on my iphone. i obviously wasn’t taking my canon in the shower lol. as a photographer without the money to upgrade i try to remind others you can be creative with what you have. the best camera is the one you have with you ❤️ #mentalhealthawareness #ptsdrecovery #sexualassaultsurvivor #metoo #ptsdsurvivor

text: först skulle jag vilja tacka alla som prenumererar på min kanal - jätteroligt att ni vill kolla på mitt content och mina videos. jag gillar verkligen vad jag gör och att ni uppskattar det :). men självklart finns det en baksida till det här. att lägga upp videos på youtube är fantastiskt då man kan träffa nya människor och prata med dem genom sina videos. men youtube lämnar det också möjligt att vara anonym, vilket kan resultera i kommentarer som dem ovan. att få hat är helt enkelt något man får ta. att få höra att man ska dö brutalt från en främling rör mig faktiskt inte ryggen - jag känner inte den här personen och sättet han (tror jag) uttrycker sig är relativt barnsligt. men är det okej - nej. för någon månad sedan fick jag, tillsammans med kommentaren ovan, höra att ”du måste fixa silikonpattar för att en titty-streamer måste ha stora pattar”. och det var här jag insåg att mitt kön började spela roll. att höra att man brutalt ska dö är fortfarande inte okej, men där spelar inte mitt kön in. jag får alltså höra att jag ska skaffa silikon pattar för att jag är tjej och håller på med gaming, då ”titty-streamer” är en tjej som ofta spelar spel och visar hud. fortfarande så rör inte kommentarerna mig ryggen - jag blir inte sårad av det. men det som rör mig ryggen är sexismen bakom det. om jag skulle varit av det motsatta könet hade jag inte fått den kommentaren. hatet hade fortfarande varit med, men utan det sexuella. mitt kön spelar alltså en tydlig roll. jag blir behandlad annorlunda för att jag är tjej. något som för övrigt inte är ovanligt för offentliga tjejer. tydlig bevis på att det finns sexism mot tjejer i vardagen. inte någon ”breaking discovery” kanske. men det var inte det jag ville visa med inlägget. det jag vill visa är att det finns - men det stoppar inte mig.
name: Greta Nygren

text:
it was a wild ride to financial independence retire early (fire). but at 35, i did it! 
there were several times when the emergency fund came in handy. 
in light of #metoo + #timesup, i was able to leave toxic work environments in a matter of days. 
i hope everyone in our community has an emergency fund in place. 
an emergency fund is also known as f-you money. 
hopefully you won't ever need to touch it! 
but if you do + end up sayin' f-you to the employer, i want to hear about it! 
either way, always love hearing about ppl's journey to fire.

my adventure continues as i aim to create wealth beyond money:

text:
it took me and is actually still taking me a long time to rebuild my self worth. for a long time i thought i was only worth the body i was in. merely a toy to be used as pleased, called when needed and told to shut up when i had an opinion of my own. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
i sent four years trapped in a relationship where i was isolated from friends and family, watched, belittled, called crazy, stupid and emotional. i felt i couldn’t leave the person i was with, i was total dependant on them. made to be, that’s the way they keep you trapped.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
people have often questioned why i didn’t get out earlier. but i couldn’t, my soul had been pushed out of me and i’d been ground into dirt. nothing but a pile of worthless dirt. the day i did break it off, i had a full blown panic attack. that was one of the hardest days of my life. but that tiny second of light i saw was enough for me to get out.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
people can get great joy out of wearing a person down, and will just move onto the next victim. unfortunately for you, it’s not so easy to say “next”.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
my self worth will forever more be a battle i have to tackle. although it is much better, i still find in quite moments, questioning whether i still might just be a pile of dirt... ______________________________

text:
after two years of labor, on this final day of fall — a magical day of solstice — here it is!!! my lil intersectional feminist rager!! bop if u tired of being degraded while u get down! 💓 “fall back” is basically my way of saying #metoo and finally clapping back at rappers who been dissin females since the induction of the genre. rap should be radical and progressive. you dont have to put women down to make rap music‼️ also this song aint anti-men 😒 so many talented dudes helped bring this to life from graphic designer @histooo to photog @christogram to sound engineers at @spitshinemusic 💞

when i first started rapping, i was told to be more aggressive. i wasn’t mad at the criticism, as i sought it out. i didn’t see it at the time, but i was caught in a feedback loop that kept me from creating. now that i’m out of that space, i can thank those who shared that sentiment for the motivation. i also want to thank those who gave this track a preview and for gassin this shy girl up! my dms and comments are open if you want to discuss this project respeckfully ✨💖 “fall back” is on all streaming platforms now! search smoki daze, babe 💕💗💘 *oh ps if u fam and follow me, the revolution is explicit. sorry!

text:
män blir verkligen upprörda när de plötsligt begriper att kvinnor pratar med varandra om dem. iaf om de misstänker att man ”kränker deras integritet”, dvs berättar något personligt om dem. det blev så himla tydligt iom #metoo, vilka oändliga protester som hördes från män. ”nej prata inte om oss om det inte är smicker!!!” skrek de. och vilken kraft i systerskapet när det visade sig att jag med och hon med och du med! delade beska erfarenheter. erfarenheter av övergrepp. erfarenheter av våld. erfarenheter av män som går över gränserna. och hur hemligt vanligt vi tycker det är. jag minns att jag tänkte att jag nog inte blivit utsatt för övergrepp. sen mindes jag rolling stones-konserten när jag var kanske 14, och hur en man i 30-årsåldern tryckte sin erigerade kuk mot min rumpa. och gången när jag blev påhoppad på hemväg. och gången när en vilt främmande man tog sig in i min lägenhet, stal mina veteskorpor, hotade att våldta mig och slutligen misshandlade mig så att min trumhinna sprack. .
.
för några veckor sedan la jag ut en fråga i sociala medier om vilka artister folk legat med. jag tyckte det var en rolig idé att samla allt i en låtlista. jag fick enbart glada tillrop från kvinnor, även av kvinnor som själva är artister. männen i de sociala flödena blev oroliga dock. borde jag inte tänka på vad jag utsätter artisterna för? är det inte ett brott mot pul? det kan inte vara så roligt för artisterna att hamna på en sån lista!! tyckte männen, då. 
det slog mig. de fattar inte att vi pratar med varandra. och det är det stora hotet. kvinnor som pratar med varandra. 
om man huvudsakligen är snäll, då behöver man inte oroa sig så fasligt över att folk pratar om en. detta verkar vara skrämmande för flera män. och stärkande för många kvinnor. .
.
här är den iaf. över 100 pers skickade in bidrag. tydlig övervikt bland indiekillarna från 90-talet (👋🏼👋🏼👋🏼 #broderdaniel 😂), men det beror ju på det demografiska underlaget. sedan ett par  överraskningar faktiskt! håll till godo! länk i instastory!

text: flashback friday lol operation cookie monster lol this was on my first deployment in 2005-06.  we were operating in the village of shihobi, outside of fallujah, iraq.  we had set up a patrol base and had begun patrolling ops.  the en quickly figured out and set up a complex ambush using a school, and a old dump truck as an armored vehicle.  i had just gotten off patrol, my pack was still on the side of this truck.  i had fresh cookies and a carton of cowboy killers in it!  i closed my eyes for a min only to be awoken by a rpg volley and mg fire.  our squad leader rushed us out of the building.  as we ran into oncoming fire marines on the roof established fire superiority with 240’s and m203’s we systematically cleared the village.  if it breathed it died lol they took my cookies and smokes but we took their lives 💀

text:
if you've ever felt sad
if you've ever felt alone
like a fuckin alien because some idiot, decided to touch you like an object, talk to you like an object, you are not alone.

i am young, i am young and dumb like everyone else. people may think us small, insignificant, silly- but we are fucking brilliant. i'm sick of being quiet, i'm sick of suffering in silence, so i'd like to present a project that's sprung to mind, i've been wanting to do something to raise awareness and support of those who've been assaulted.. but i never know how or where to start.  if you reference, my previous post about assault-the positivity and support it gained was unimaginable.

i have never felt so strong, so powerful, so.. human, happily human- sense my assault which was three plus years ago.

so i want you, to share your stories. you don't have to go in detail, hell, just say "i'm ____ and i've been assaulted/harrassed." i want to make a movement. to spread awareness. to post that yes, it happens- but no.. no we are not quiet. we are not good little victims we are not dead we are not broken we are just struggling.

but we come out stronger than anyone can imagine.

and maybe you find me 'extra' maybe you find me an 'attention whore' milking assault for attention. but i call this rebellion, i call this decency, i call this a cry of love and hope into a bareen wasteland of.. of silence. of people who are so painfully polarized 
give this project a name, give it a home comment, message me, tag me in posts, tag yungblud, tag you're friends, tag ian, i want to see you're polygraph eyes! i want to see your scars! i want you to understand that those scars are battle wounds not detrimental markers of him or her. 
if anyone is interested in helping out with this project, message me as well. i'm going to post more details on this soon, loves 🖤

i love you.
we love you.
this is what the black hearts club looks like.
this is what the mother fuckin' youth looks like.
✊🖤

text:
i was standing 
before 
you,
wearing my skin only
and you touched my nudity, 
as you left some burns.
my body is a temple, 
it is transcendent, 
but it shrunk under your gaze,
so brutally tender
and i got lost in the maze of its chambers.

out of my dignity,
you were stripping me slowly,
out of my dignity and out of my mind
so if you spit in a temple, 
will it seize to be holly?
will it seize to be a shelter 
for something sacred,
for something i used to call “soul”? at home i washed my skin 
and i hung it to dry,
then my angels laid down
to console my demons, 
to say we are as clean as 
before 
you. (17.07.17) #poetry #metoo #canva

text_retweet:
@regran_ed from @toniabruisedbutnotbroken - 😭😭😭😭😭😭😭😭😭😭#repost @isuvoa (@get_repost)
・・・
#whyididntreport 
because i was 8 years old and i was scared and ashamed of what was being done to me. the people that sexually abused me as a child were my family members. it was my grandmother and my biological father. i was 14 years old when i reported to the police that my father had sexually abused me for 5 years. my family immediately disowned me. they didn’t believe me and they protected my father. i was unwanted and abandoned by everyone. the police believed me because there was sufficient physical evidence of the abuse. but i never mentioned my grandmother’s sexual abuse because i didn’t think that her sexual assault counted as sexual abuse. there was no real penetration just oral copulation and touching by my grandmother.  however, the judicial system always looks for “evidence” and there was no evidence to prove what my grandmother had done to me when i was 8 years old. there are many reasons that survivors don’t tell anyone about the sexual abuse or the rape inflicted upon them. it’s been many years after the sexual abuse and i recently had a flashback of my father sexually abusing me when i was three years old. i will never be able to tell you when the sexual abuse begun as a child. i can’t tell you the time, what he/she was wearing during each assault on me. i can’t give you a chronological timeline of the events. does this make me a liar? no. i was too busy dissociating and surviving this horrific assault to my dignity, mind, body and soul.

#thereasonwhyididntreport
